Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on any exterior Tatooine site (free at Beggar's Canyon). You may use any amount of Force in the opponent's Force Pile during your turns. However, if you use more than 1 of the opponent's Force in a turn, Beggar is lost.

Title: Beru Lars
Gametext: Forfeit +2 when at same site as Owen Lars or a Hydroponics Station. If lost from table during opponent's turn, Luke is power +3 until the end of your next turn.

Title: Beru Stew
Gametext: Each player must immediately activate 2 Force. Also, you may activate 1 additional Force for each Beru Lars, Owen Lars or Hydroponics Station on table.

Title: Biggs Darklighter
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Red 3, also adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: Black 2
Gametext: May add 1 pilot.

Title: Black 3
Gametext: May add 1 pilot.

Title: Blast Door Controls
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Cancels: Into The Garbage Chute, Flyboy; Narrow Escape; Blast The Door, Kid!; and Rebel Barrier.

Title: Blaster
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value.

Title: Blaster Rack
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. At any time, you may transfer one of your character weapons from any site to the Blaster Rack. During your deploy phase, weapon may be transferred to your character on table for an expenditure of Force equal to the weapon's deploy cost.

Title: Blaster Rifle
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value.

Title: Blaster Rifle
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value.

Title: Blaster Scope
Gametext: Deploy on your non-[Permanent Weapon] blaster. Scope allows that weapon to target at an adjacent site.

Title: Boosted TIE Cannon
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your TIE Advanced x1. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Subtract 1 if targeting a capital starship. Add 1 if targeting a starfighter. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.

Title: Boring Conversation Anyway
Gametext: Cancel either: Report To Lord Vader, Scomp Link Access, Rebel Planners, Rebel Reinforcements, Gift of the Mentor, Panic, Don't Get Cocky, Skywalkers, Demotion, Combined Attack or Surprise Assault.

Title: BoShek
Gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. May make a Kessel Run in place of a smuggler. Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: C-3PO (See-Threepio)
Gametext: Total power at same site is +2 for each of your droid/Rebel pairs present, including C-3PO. R2-D2 is forfeit +2 when present.

Title: Caller
Gametext: Deploy on any Imperial or Jawa. During your control phase, may steal one droid at same site if it is controlled by a Restraining Bolt. After droid is stolen, Restraining Bolt returns to owner's hand.

Title: Caller
Gametext: Deploy on a Rebel or Jawa. During your control phase, may steal one droid at same site if it is controlled by a Restraining Bolt. After droid is stolen, Restraining Bolt returns to owner's hand.

Title: Cantina Brawl
Gametext: Use 2 Force to cause a fight to break out in the Cantina. Both players draw destiny. All characters in Cantina with an ability number matching either destiny draw are lost.

Title: Charming To The Last
Gametext: If Tarkin and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle, you may add one battle destiny (add two destiny if Rebel is Leia).

Title: Chief Bast
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Power +1 if at same site as Tarkin. If a battle was just initiated at a system where Bast is present with your non-droid character, may 'evacuate' (relocate) both to a related site.

Title: Collateral Damage
Gametext: An accident occurs at the beginning of a battle at any site where opponent has at least two characters and one weapon. Draw destiny. If destiny < number of opponent's characters at that site, one is lost. (Opponent's choice.)

Title: Collision!
Gametext: Use 1 Force if opponent has at least two starships present at same system or sector. Draw destiny. If destiny < number of those starships, opponent must lose one of them.

Title: Colonel Wullf Yularen
Gametext: Power +1 if at the same site with Tarkin, Chief Bast or General Dodonna.

Title: Combined Attack
Gametext: During a battle, target opponent's starship present with two (or more) of your starship weapons. Add all weapon destiny draws together. Apply that total separately for each weapon in an order of your choosing.

Title: Comlink
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any character. If opponent has just initiated a battle or Force drain at Comlink's location or an adjacent site, you may 'react' by deploying cards (at normal use of the Force) to that battle or Force drain location.

Title: Commander Praji
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Devastator, also adds 1 to hyperspeed. Where present, cancels game text of C-3PO or R2-D2.

Title: Corellian Corvette
Gametext: May add 3 pilots, 4 passengers and 1 vehicle. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Counter Assault
Gametext: Use 1 Force to cancel a Force drain at one location. Draw one destiny for each character, starship and vehicle the opponent has present. Compare your destiny total to opponent's power total. Player with lowest total loses Force equal to the difference.

Title: Crash Site Memorial
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. If you just lost a vehicle, droid, weapon, or device, may stack it here. Once during your deploy phase, you may exchange any one card in hand with one card stacked here. Any cards stacked here are considered 'supporting.'

Title: CZ-3 (Seezee-Three)
Gametext: If opponent has just initiated a battle or Force drain at CZ-3's location or an adjacent site, you may 'react' by deploying cards (at normal use of the Force) to that battle or Force drain location.

Title: Dantooine
DarkSideText: Your starships may move here as a 'react'.

Title: Dantooine
DarkSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.
LightSideText: Your capital starships deploy -2 and your starfighters deploy -1 here.

Title: Dark Collaboration
Gametext: If Tarkin and either Tagge or Motti are in a battle together, you may add two battle destiny. OR Cancel Restricted Deployment or Rebel Barrier.

Title: Dark Hours
Gametext: Deploy on a site under "nighttime conditions." One at a time, target each non-droid character here and draw destiny. If destiny > ability, character 'sleeps' until end of your next turn (power, forfeit, and ability = 0, game text is canceled, and may not pilot, drive, or move). At the end of your next turn, lost Effect.

Title: Dark Jedi Lightsaber
Gametext: Use X Force to deploy on your warrior where X = (7 - warrior's ability). May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature using X Force. Draw two destiny. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.

Title: Dark Jedi Presence
Gametext: If one of your Dark Jedi is present during any battle, use 1 Force to cause all other Imperials there to battle at double power.

Title: Dark Maneuvers
Gametext: Add 2 to maneuver and 1 to power of any starfighter for the remainder of this turn. If it has hyperdrive, also add 2 to hyperspeed. (Interrupt may even affect the result immediately after a destiny draw targeting the starfighter's maneuver.)

Title: Darth Vader
Gametext: When in battle, adds 1 to each of your battle destiny draws. Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots (or 4 to power and 3 to maneuver if Vader's Custom TIE). Immune to attrition < 5.

Title: Dathcha
Gametext: * To deploy, requires 2 Force from each players' Force Pile. Cannot deploy otherwise. Deploy only on Tatooine, but may move elsewhere. Power +2 at non-Tatooine sites.

Title: Dead Jawa
Gametext: If two or more stormtroopers are present where the opponent has Jawas, target as many Jawas there as desired. Draw destiny. If destiny > the number of Jawas you targeted, they are immediately lost.

Title: Death Star Plans
Gametext: Deploy on any Death Star site (except docking bay). Target one of your droids (not on Death Star). When target reaches Utinni Effect, 'steal' plans. If target then moves to any Yavin 4 site, draw 3 destiny. Retrieve that much lost Force. Lose Utinni Effect.

Title: Death Star Sentry
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Death Star site. Declare one of the following to affect that site and adjacent sites while 'sentry' present: Opponent's deploy +1. OR Opponent's ability required for battle destiny +1. OR Your total power +1.

Title: Death Star Trooper
Gametext: Deploy only on Death Star, but may move elsewhere. Power -1 at a site other than a Death Star site.

Title: Death Star: Central Core
DarkSideText: If you control, Wrong Turn and Retract The Bridge deploy for free.
LightSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here and Death Star Tractor Beam is canceled.

Title: Death Star: Detention Block Control Room
LightSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here and all imprisoned characters on Death Star are released.

Title: Death Star: Detention Block Corridor
DarkSideText: Add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws here.
LightSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.

Title: Death Star: Docking Bay 327
DarkSideText: Your docking bay transit from here is free.
LightSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.

Title: Death Star: Docking Bay 327
DarkSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
LightSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.

Title: Death Star: Level 4 Military Corridor
DarkSideText: During your move phase, Imperials may move free from here to any one Death Star site.
LightSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.

Title: Death Star: Trash Compactor
LightSideText: You may deploy here without presence. If you control, Force drain +1 here.

Title: Death Star: War Room
DarkSideText: If you control, with a leader here, all Rebel Troopers and Y-wings on table are forfeit -1.
LightSideText: If you initiate a battle here, add one battle destiny.

Title: Demotion
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Imperial except Vader, Emperor or a stormtrooper. That Imperial is power -2 and its game text is canceled.

Title: Devastator
Gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 2.

Title: Dice Ibegon
Gametext: If present where an opponent's character just fired a weapon, may use 1 Force to utilize Dice's poison stinger (once per turn). Target that character and draw destiny. If destiny = ability, target is 'hit.'

Title: Disarmed
Gametext: If both players have a character with a weapon present at same site, deploy on that opponent's character during any control phase. Character loses all weapons, is power -1 and may no longer carry weapons. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Disarmed
Gametext: If both players have a character with a weapon present at same site, deploy on that opponent's character during any control phase. Character loses all weapons, is power -1 and may no longer carry weapons. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Djas Puhr
Gametext: Power +1 for each (Dark Side Force icon) present, +2 under "nighttime conditions." Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: Don't Get Cocky
Gametext: If Luke and Han are in a battle together, you may add two battle destiny. OR If opponent just initiated a battle at a system or sector, choose one TIE/ln present to be lost.

Title: Don't Underestimate Our Chances
Gametext: If an opponent has just initiated a battle, triple the resulting battle damage for the eventual loser. OR Triple the result of You Overestimate Their Chances.

Title: Dr. Evazan
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. The not-so-good doctor may 'operate' on any other character present that was just 'hit' or just Disarmed; 'patient' is lost.

Title: Droid Detector
Gametext: Deploy at any interior site. Cannot be moved. Droids may not deploy to same site. Following the turn this device is deployed, all droids present are lost at end of any turn.

Title: Droid Shutdown
Gametext: Cancel an attempt by opponent to target your droid to be stolen, 'hit,' lost or captured. Droid is protected from all such attempts for remainder of turn.

Title: DS-61-2
Gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 2, also adds 1 to maneuver and may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: DS-61-3
Gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 3, also adds 1 to maneuver and may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: Dutch
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Gold 1, also adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Adds 1 to forfeit of each other Gold Squadron pilot at same location.

Title: EG-6 (Eegee-Six)
Gametext: Adds 1 to power of each of your droids present, except power droids. * Destiny equals zero, but if drawn as a battle destiny where you have less power than opponent, your total power present is doubled (once per battle).

Title: Electrobinoculars
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any warrior. At any time, you may peek at the top card of your Reserve Deck by using 2 Force. You may choose to move that card to the top of your Force Pile.

Title: Elis Helrot
Gametext: At any time (except during battle), target any or all of your characters at one site to 'transport' (relocate) to any one other site. Draw destiny. Use that much Force to 'transport,' or place Interrupt in Lost Pile.

Title: Ellorrs Madak
Gametext: Deploy on your non-pilot character (except droids) to give that character pilot ([Pilot]) skill. Adds 2 to power of anything that character pilots. OR Deploy on your pilot. Adds 1 to power of anything that character pilots. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Emergency Deployment
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle where opponent has more than double your power, reveal up to 3 cards from your Reserve Deck. Of those 3, deploy anywhere (for free) any characters, starships, vehicles, devices or weapons. Any others are lost.

Title: Escape Pod
Gametext: Save all characters, weapons, and devices aboard any just-lost capital starship. Relocate them to any planet site.

Title: Evacuate?
Gametext: Unless Tarkin is aboard, save all characters, weapons and devices aboard any just-lost capital starship. Relocate them to any one planet site or one of your capital starships.

Title: Expand The Empire
Gametext: Deploy on any site. 'Expands' your "game text" for that site to add to your "game text" at the adjacent sites.

Title: Eyes In The Dark
Gametext: Deploy beside either player's Lost Pile. That pile is turned face down. Cards from that player's Life Force may not be viewed when they are lost.

Title: Fear Will Keep Them In Line
Gametext: Deploy on any capital starship. When that starship is at a system or sector you control, your total power is +1 in battles at related sites.

Title: Feltipern Trevagg
Gametext: While no droid present with Trevagg, to initiate battles at same location as Trevagg, player must use X Force, where X = total number of (Dark Side Force icon) icons and (Light Side Force icon) icons present.

Title: Figrin D'an
Gametext: Once each turn during your control phase, you may use 1 Force to make a 'wager.' Draw three destiny. Opponent draws two destiny. Player with highest total may randomly select one card to be retrieved from that player's Lost Pile.

Title: Friendly Fire
Gametext: An accident occurs at the beginning of a battle at any site where opponent has at least two characters and one weapon. Draw destiny. If destiny < number of opponent's characters at that site, one is lost. (Opponent's choice.)

Title: Full Scale Alert
Gametext: Use 2 Force. Draw Destiny. If destiny < number of Stormtroopers on the table, all opponent's movement is blocked for the remainder of this turn (except for smugglers and the starships they are aboard).

Title: Full Throttle
Gametext: If your pilot (or permanent pilot) is defending a battle alone at a system or sector, add one battle destiny. OR If Luke is defending a battle alone at a system or sector, add 1 to power and add one battle destiny.

Title: Fusion Generator Supply Tanks
Gametext: Deploy on your starship at a system or sector where a related docking bay is on table. Adds 1 to hyperspeed, power and maneuver.

Title: Fusion Generator Supply Tanks
Gametext: Deploy on your starship at a system or sector where a related docking bay is on table. Adds 1 to hyperspeed, power and maneuver.

Title: Gaderffii Stick
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Tusken Raider. If a battle has just been initiated where present, target a character for free; draw two destiny. If total destiny > 5, target's weapons are 'knocked away' (may not be used this battle).

Title: Garindan
Gametext: When at same location as a Rebel of ability > 2, deploy -1 there for any Imperials, and during your move phase, Imperials at an adjacent site may move there for free.

Title: General Dodonna
Gametext: Increases Rebel Planners by 1, doubles if at same site. May use 1 Force to cancel Wrong Turn. Each Rebel present with him at a Yavin 4 site is power +1.

Title: General Tagge
Gametext: Tagge's forfeit +1 for each Imperial trooper, of any kind, present with him at a site.

Title: Gift Of The Mentor
Gametext: If Luke and Obi-Wan or Yoda are in a battle together, you may add two battle destiny. OR Use 1 Force to search through your Reserve Deck and take any one lightsaber into your hand. Shuffle deck, cut and replace.

Title: Gold 1
Gametext: May add 2 pilots or passengers.

Title: Gold 5
Gametext: May add 2 pilots or passengers, and 1 astromech.

Title: Grand Moff Tarkin
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When with Vader in a battle, once per battle may cancel one opponent's destiny just drawn.

Title: Gravel Storm
Gametext: Strikes at Dune Sea, Jundland Wastes, Beggar's Canyon, Lars' Moisture Farm, Jawa Camp, or Mos Eisley. Target opponent's character at that site. Draw destiny. Target lost if destiny > ability.

Title: Han Seeker
Gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Han (or alien) of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an "all cards" situation). Seeker is also lost.

Title: Han Solo
Gametext: Once during battle, may use 1 Force to cancel and re-draw your just drawn destiny. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Falcon, also adds 2 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: Han's Back
Gametext: If Han is lost, use 1 Force to retrieve him from the Lost Pile. OR Use 3 Force to search through your Reserve Deck and take Han into your hand. Shuffle deck, cut and replace.

Title: Han's Dice
Gametext: If one of your characters of ability > 2 is in a battle, use 1 Force to draw another battle destiny instead of the one you just drew.

Title: Han's Heavy Blaster Pistol
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on Han, or 3 on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. If hit by Han, target's forfeit = 0.

Title: Hear Me Baby, Hold Together
Gametext: If opponent just targeted your starship with a starship weapon, subtract 2 from each of that weapon's destiny draws.

Title: Help Me Obi-Wan Kenobi
Gametext: If Obi-Wan is at a site you control, he may apply any amount of his ability toward drawing a battle destiny at any other location. Ability he uses this way cannot be used again this turn. OR One Rebel may move as a 'react' to an adjacent battle site.

Title: How Did We Get Into This Mess?
Gametext: If one of your droids is at the Dune Sea or where there is a Scomp link, use 1 Force to discard your entire hand to your Used Pile. Draw the same number of cards from your Reserve Deck. Draw one extra card if droid is C-3PO or R2-D2.

Title: Hydroponics Station
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any exterior Tatooine site. Cannot be moved. The first Force you activate during your activate phase may be drawn into hand instead. If a Vaporator on table, the second Force you activate may also be drawn into hand.

Title: Hyper Escape
Gametext: Cancel a battle just initiated at any system or sector by moving all your starships and vehicles there away.

Title: I Find Your Lack Of Faith Disturbing
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on one of your Dark Jedi. While present at a site, unless a Jedi is also present, opponent's total ability at same location is reduced by 2.

Title: I Have You Now
Gametext: If a Dark Jedi and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle, you may add one battle destiny (add two destiny if Rebel is Luke).

Title: I've Got A Bad Feeling About This
Gametext: If you just initiated a battle at a location where you have less power than the opponent, double opponent's battle damage if you win the battle (if Han is present at the battle location, triple opponent's battle damage).

Title: I've Got A Problem Here
Gametext: Use 1 Force to target opponent's starfighter with maneuver at a system or sector where a battle just finished. Draw destiny. Starfighter lost if destiny > maneuver.

Title: I've Lost Artoo!
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on a starship with a [Nav Computer] or astromech aboard. Target [Nav computer] or astromech and draw destiny. If destiny > 1, astromech lost (lose Effect) or [Nav Computer] is canceled (may add 1 astromech); otherwise, Effect lost.

Title: Imperial Barrier
Gametext: Use 1 Force to prevent any character or starship just deployed by the opponent from battling or moving for the remainder of this turn.

Title: Imperial Blaster
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value.

Title: Imperial Code Cylinder
Gametext: If any Imperial leader is present with a Scomp link, you may: Glance at the cards in any Reserve Deck for 20 seconds. Shuffle, cut and replace. OR If also at a Death Star site, cancel Scomp Link Access or Into The Garbage Chute, Flyboy.

Title: Imperial Pilot
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.

Title: Imperial Reinforcements
Gametext: If opponent has more total characters and starships on table than you have, use 1 Force to draw destiny. Retrieve that number of Stormtroopers and/or TIE/lns.

Title: Imperial Trooper Guard
Gametext: Power +4 when defending a battle. Cannot move.

Title: Imperial-Class Star Destroyer
Gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Into The Garbage Chute, Flyboy
Gametext: If Trash Compactor is on table, cancel any battle just initiated at another Death Star site by moving (for free) all your characters involved to the Trash Compactor.

Title: Ion Cannon
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny +2 > defense value, all starship weapons deployed on target are lost, armor or maneuver = 0 and hyperspeed = 0.

Title: It Could Be Worse
Gametext: If you must lose Force for any reason, reduce the loss by X amount by using X Force.

Title: It's Worse
Gametext: If It Could Be Worse was just played, it is canceled and you may use X Force to raise damage against opponent by X amount. OR If opponent just lost Force from a battle, play to increase loss by 1 Force.

Title: Jawa
Gametext: * To deploy, requires 1 Force from each players' Force Pile. Cannot deploy otherwise. Deploy only on Tatooine, but may move elsewhere.

Title: Jawa
Gametext: * To deploy, requires 1 Force from each players' Force Pile. Cannot deploy otherwise. Deploy only on Tatooine, but may move elsewhere.

Title: Jawa Pack
Gametext: To deploy (on your side of table), requires 3 Force from both players' Force Piles. Cannot deploy otherwise. All your Jawas are forfeit +1.

Title: Jawa Siesta
Gametext: To deploy (on your side of table), requires 3 Force from both players' Force Piles. Cannot deploy otherwise. All your Jawas are forfeit +1.

Title: Jedi Lightsaber
Gametext: Use X Force to deploy on your warrior where X = (7 - warrior's ability). May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature by using X Force. Draw two destiny. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.

Title: Jedi Presence
Gametext: If one of your Jedi is present during any battle, use 1 Force to cause all other Rebels there to battle at double power.

Title: Jek Porkins
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Red 6, also adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: Juri Juice
Gametext: Deploy on any alien if Cantina, Mos Eisley or Jabba's Sail Barge on table. That alien may not use ability in battles (if Kabe, she also cannot 'steal'). Utinni Effect canceled by moving that alien to one of those sites without 'driving' a vehicle.

Title: K'lor'slug
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. For each unit of ability you have present during a battle, you may use 1 Force to raise your total power by 1. Ability used in this way cannot also be used to draw destiny.

Title: Kabe
Gametext: During your control phase, may target one opponent's weapon or device at same site. Draw destiny. If destiny < target's destiny number, Kabe 'steals' device to use, or weapon to hold and transfer (for free) to a warrior at same site.

Title: Kal'Falnl C'ndros
Gametext: When in a battle, if both players draw only one battle destiny and yours is higher, reduces opponent's destiny to zero. Landspeed = 3. Adds 2 to power of anything she pilots. May not be aboard starfighters or enclosed vehicles.

Title: Kessel
DarkSideText: Your starships deploy -1 here, -2 if Tarkin is aboard a starship here. If you control, Kessel Run is canceled.
LightSideText: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.

Title: Kessel
DarkSideText: If you control, Kessel Run is prevented (canceled).
LightSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.

Title: Kessel Run
Gametext: Deploy on Kessel. Target one of your smugglers at another system. X = parsec distance between the two systems. When target reaches Kessel, opponent draws destiny. If = 0, starship lost. Otherwise, by returning to first system, 'retrieve' X Lost Force. Lose Utinni Effect.

Title: Ket Maliss
Gametext: Deploy on your non-warrior character (except droids) to give that character warrior ([Warrior]) skill. OR Deploy on your warrior. That character is power +1. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Kintan Strider
Gametext: If opponent just forfeited or lost a character, use 1 Force to regenerate one of your own characters. Retrieve the character closest to the top of your Lost Pile into your hand.

Title: Kitik Keed'kak
Gametext: Immediately lost if at same site as overprotective mother, Kal'Falnl C'ndros. Cannot board starfighters or enclosed vehicles.

Title: Krayt Dragon Howl
Gametext: If Obi-Wan is defending a battle alone at a site, add 1 to power and add one battle destiny. OR If any other Rebel with ability > 2 is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny.

Title: Labria
Gametext: Once each turn, during your control phase, you may reveal the top card of your Reserve Deck to both players. If it is a vehicle or starship, card is immediately lost. Otherwise, return it to the top of your Reserve Deck, Force Pile or Used Pile.

Title: Laser Projector
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on an interior sire. May target a seeker (use defense value = 1), character or creature for free. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny -1 > defense value. Laser Projector may be targeted by any weapon (use defense value = 1).

Title: Lateral Damage
Gametext: Deploy on any system. Target an opponent's starship. Target's power and forfeit = 0. When target reaches Utinni Effect, target draws one destiny. Utinni Effect canceled if destiny > 2. Otherwise, draw again next move phase, etc.

Title: Leesub Sirln
Gametext: Once each turn during your control phase, may use 1 Force to guess a card type and point to a card in opponent's hand. Card must be shown. If guessed correctly, card is lost.

Title: Leia Organa
Gametext: Adds 1 to power of each Rebel present with her at a Death Star site. 'Diplomatic' immunity to attrition < 2.

Title: Leia's Back
Gametext: If Leia is lost, use 1 Force to retrieve her from the Lost Pile. OR Use 3 Force to search through your Reserve Deck and take Leia into your hand. Shuffle deck, cut and replace.

Title: Leia's Sporting Blaster
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on Leia, or 2 on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle for free. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny -1 > defense value. If hit by Leia, target's forfeit = 0.

Title: Lieutenant Tanbris
Gametext: Deploy -1 for starship weapons of any starship he pilots. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Subtracts 1 from maneuver of any starfighter he pilots.

Title: Lift Tube
Gametext: May carry 4 passengers. Deploy and move only at interior mobile sites. May move without presence aboard. Also, may move as a 'react' only to a battle or Force drain (if within range).

Title: Lift Tube
Gametext: May carry 4 passengers. Deploy and move only at interior mobile sites. May move without presence aboard. Also, may move as a 'react' only to a battle or Force drain (if within range).

Title: Light Repeating Blaster Rifle
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your warrior. If your power droid or fusion generator present, may target a character, creature or vehicle using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. May fire repeatedly for 2 Force each time.

Title: Lightsaber Proficiency
Gametext: Deploy on your character with ability > 2 and a lightsaber. That character is power +3 in battles or may add 1 to Force drain where present. Effect is lost if character loses lightsaber.

Title: Limited Resources
Gametext: If the opponent has two cards or less in hand, opponent must immediately lose 2 Force (4 Force if it is your turn). If the opponent has Fusion Generator Supply Tanks aboard a starship, loss is reduced by 2.

Title: LIN-V8K (Elleyein-Veeatekay)
Gametext: At any time during your turn, may use 1 Force to 'defuse' (lose) any one mine at same site.

Title: LIN-V8M (Elleyein-Veeateemm)
Gametext: At any time during your turn, may use 1 Force to 'defuse' (lose) any one mine at same site.

Title: Local Trouble
Gametext: Use 1 Force at the beginning of your battle phase to allow any two of your Stormtroopers in the Cantina to battle any one opponent's character (your choice). You may add one battle destiny. No other battles may occur in Cantina this turn.

Title: Lone Pilot
Gametext: If your pilot (or permanent pilot) is defending a battle alone at a system or sector, add one battle destiny. OR If Motti is defending a battle alone at a system or sector, add two battle destiny.

Title: Lone Warrior
Gametext: If any warrior is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny. OR If Tagge is defending a battle alone at a site, add two battle destiny.

Title: Look Sir, Droids
Gametext: Use 1 Force to search through the opponent's Used Pile and move any droids you find there to opponent's Lost Pile. OR Use X Force to destroy any one droid on table where X = droid's deploy cost.

Title: Luke Seeker
Gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Luke of ability < 4 or pilot of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an "all cards" situation). Seeker is also lost.

Title: Luke Skywalker
Gametext: While Luke is not on Tatooine your total Force generation is +1. Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Red 5, also adds 2 to maneuver. Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: Luke? Luuuuke!
Gametext: Deploy on any Tatooine site. Target any Rebel. Target is power and forfeit -1 (-3 if target is Luke). If Rebel's forfeit reaches zero, Rebel is lost. Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.

Title: Luke's Back
Gametext: If Luke is lost, use 1 Force to retrieve him from the Lost Pile. OR Use 3 Force to search through your Reserve Deck and take Luke into your hand. Shuffle deck, cut and replace.

Title: Luke's X-34 Landspeeder
Gametext: May add 1 driver and 2 passengers. Moves free if Luke aboard. May move as a 'react'.

Title: M'iiyoom Onith
Gametext: Once during each of your control phases, may reveal opponent's hand by using X Force, where X = number of cards in opponent's hand. All unique (•) male Rebels and unique (•) male aliens there are lost.

Title: Macroscan
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy near opponent's Reserve Deck. At any time, you may use 1 Force to peek at the top card of that deck. If "nighttime conditions" exist anywhere on table, you may peek at the top three cards.

Title: Mantellian Savrip
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on your side of table (free if C-3PO on table). After losing any battle: characters, starships and vehicles may be forfeited directly from your hand (for forfeit value) to reduce attrition or battle damage.

Title: Millennium Falcon
Gametext: May add 2 pilots and 2 passengers. Immune to attrition < 5 if Han, Chewie or Lando piloting. Has ship-docking capability.

Title: Molator
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. For each unit of ability you have present during a battle, you may use 1 Force to raise your total power by 1. Ability used in this way cannot also be used to draw destiny.

Title: Momaw Nadon
Gametext: During your control phase, may snare (steal) one Bantha, Dewback, Wampa, Rancor, Bubo, or Dragonsnake present at same site.

Title: Moment Of Triumph
Gametext: If Tarkin is defending a battle alone, add two battle destiny. OR If any alien is defending a battle alone, add one battle destiny.

Title: Move Along...
Gametext: iIf a battle was just initiated at a site where your Jedi is present, use 1 Force to draw destiny; that number of opponent's characters with ability = 1 (your choice) must each move away (for free), or be lost.

Title: MSE-6 'Mouse' Droid
Gametext: Landspeed = 3. Deploys to same site as a character targeted by a Utinni Effect (except Kessel Run). If this droid 'reaches' Utinni Effect, may relocate it here. Upon delivery, 'mouse' droid returns to your hand.

Title: Myo
Gametext: Power +1 if present with Lirin Car'n or any bounty hunter. If lost or forfeited as a result of a battle, Myo 'regenerates' (place on top of your Used Pile).

Title: Nabrun Leids
Gametext: At any time (except during battle), target any or all of your characters at one site to 'transport' (relocate) to any one other site. Draw destiny. Use that much Force to 'transport,' or place Interrupt in Lost Pile.

Title: Narrow Escape
Gametext: If opponent just initiated battle at a site where you have a Rebel of ability > 2 present, move all of your cards with ability there away (using their landspeed).

Title: Nevar Yalnal
Gametext: If both players have a spy at same site, draw destiny. Add 2 if opponent's spy is Undercover. Opponent's spy is lost if destiny > 2.

Title: Nightfall
Gametext: Deploy on any planet system to cause "nighttime conditions" at related sites. During battles there, both sides add one destiny to power only. Spies deploy free to sites under "nighttime conditions."

Title: Noble Sacrifice
Gametext: If opponent just deployed a character, sacrifice (out of play) from table one of your characters with the same power (even a captured character). You may retrieve Force from Lost Pile equal to your sacrificed character's forfeit value.

Title: Obi-Wan Kenobi
Gametext: When a battle was just initiated where present, may use 1 Force to choose one opponent's character of ability = 1 present to move away (for free), or that character is lost. Immune to attrition < 5.

Title: Obi-Wan's Cape
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Rebel or alien. Character is immune to attrition < 5. Also, when a battle was just initiated where present, may use 1 Force to choose one opponent's character of ability = 1 present to move away (for free), or that character is lost.

Title: Obi-Wan's Lightsaber
Gametext: Deploy on Obi-Wan. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.

Title: Observation Holocam
Gametext: Deploy on a site. Adds 1 to the total weapon destiny of each of your automated weapons at same or adjacent sites. During battle, may add the power of one of your characters at an adjacent site you control to your total.

Title: Old Ben
Gametext: Use 1 Force if any of your characters (except Obi-Wan) was just forfeited from a Tatooine site. Mysterious "crazy wizard" steps in and revives (returns from Lost Pile) that character back to same site.

Title: Ommni Box
Gametext: Shuffle any player's Reserve Deck or Lost Pile or Used Pile.

Title: On The Edge
Gametext: Use 1 Force and target one Rebel (on table) of ability > 2. Choose a number from 1 to 6. You may retrieve that amount from your Lost Pile if you now draw destiny > chosen number. If you fail, Rebel is lost.

Title: Organa's Ceremonial Necklace
Gametext: Deploy on any Yavin 4 site. Target one Imperial. When Imperial reaches target site, 'steal' necklace. Whenever necklace is present during Force drain: add 1 to Force drain and may then pass (for free) to an adjacent site you control (if any), and so on.

Title: Our Most Desperate Hour
Gametext: Deploy on Alderaan. Target one Rebel at Tatooine. When Target reaches Utinni Effect, retrieve one lost Force for each Force-Attuned character you have on table, two for each Force-Sensitive or Jedi. Lose Utinni Effect.

Title: Out Of Nowhere
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle at a system or sector where you have a starship with maneuver > 3, use 1 Force to add one battle destiny.

Title: Overload
Gametext: Target any weapon (except a Gaderffii Stick or any Ewok weapon). Draw destiny. Weapon lost if destiny < weapon's destiny number. If destiny = 0, the character or starship carrying weapon is also lost.

Title: Owen Lars
Gametext: Deploys free at Lars' Moisture Farm. Power +2 if at same site as Beru Lars or a Vaporator. If lost from table during opponent's turn, Luke is power +3 until the end of your next turn.

Title: Panic
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle where opponent has more than double your power, reveal up to 3 cards from your Reserve Deck. Of those 3, deploy anywhere (for free) any characters, starships, vehicles, devices, or weapons. Any others are lost.

Title: Physical Choke
Gametext: Cause one Rebel Trooper to be immediately lost. OR If a Dark Jedi is present at a battle you have just won, use 1 Force to attempt to choke any opposing character present. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's ability, target is lost.

Title: Plastoid Armor
Gametext: Deploy on a Death Star site where a Stormtrooper was just lost. Target one of your characters not on Death Star. When target reaches Utinni Effect, relocate to target. Target is now 'disguised:' gains spy skill, power and forfeit +2, and armor = 5.

Title: Ponda Baba
Gametext: Power +3 when battling at same site as Dr. Evazan, unless opponent has a lightsaber present. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.

Title: Pops
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Gold 5, also adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: Precise Attack
Gametext: During a battle, target opponent's character or vehicle present with two (or more) of your weapons. Add all weapon destiny draws together. Apply that total separately for each weapon in an order of your choosing.

Title: Presence Of The Force
Gametext: Deploy on any location to add one (Dark Side Force icon) icon and one (Light Side Force icon) icon.

Title: Prophetess
Gametext: If you initiate a battle where present, you must predict the winner before the battle starts. If correct, randomly retrieve one lost card. If incorrect, lose 1 Force. Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: Proton Torpedoes
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your X-wing, Y-wing or B-wing. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value.

Title: Quad Laser Cannon
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Corellian Corvette or Falcon. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Add 1 if targeting a starfighter. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.

Title: R1-G4 (Arone-Geefour)
Gametext: When aboard a capital starship, adds 1 to power and hyperspeed, and that starship is immune to attrition < 3. Too large to go aboard a starfighter.

Title: R2-X2 (Artoo-Extoo)
Gametext: While aboard any starfighter, adds 1 to power, maneuver and hyperspeed.

Title: R4-E1 (Arfour-Eeone)
Gametext: While aboard a non-creature vehicle, adds 1 to power, maneuver and landspeed. May drive transport vehicles.

Title: R4-M9 (Arfour-Emmnine)
Gametext: While aboard a non-creature vehicle, adds 1 to power, maneuver and landspeed. May drive transport vehicles.

Title: Radar Scanner
Gametext: If you have at least one vehicle or starship on table, use 1 Force to glance at the cards in the opponent's hand for 10 seconds. You may move each Jawa (except Dathcha) and Tusken Raider you find there to opponent's Used Pile.

Title: Reactor Terminal
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your side of table. During your control phase, you may return any cards from your hand to the top of your Used Pile.

Title: Rebel Barrier
Gametext: Use 1 Force to prevent any character or starship just deployed by the opponent from battling or moving for the remainder of this turn.

Title: Rebel Guard
Gametext: Power +4 when defending a battle. Cannot move.

Title: Rebel Pilot
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.

Title: Rebel Planners
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy at Massassi War Room or any docking bay. Adds X to total power of your starships at the related system and related sectors, where X = the number of your starships present there.

Title: Rebel Reinforcements
Gametext: If opponent outnumbers you in total characters and starships on table, use 1 Force to draw destiny. That number of Rebel Troopers and/or Y-wings may be retrieved from Lost Pile.

Title: Rebel Trooper
Gametext: Deploys free to same site as one of your Rebels with ability > 2.

Title: Red 1
Gametext: May add 1 pilot.

Title: Red 3
Gametext: May add 1 pilot and 1 astromech.

Title: Red Leader
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Red 1, also adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Adds 1 to forfeit of each other Red Squadron pilot at same location.

Title: Restraining Bolt
Gametext: Deploy on any droid at any site. Droid cannot move and cannot utilize its "game text." During your deploy phase, Restraining Bolt may be transferred (for free) to another droid at same site.

Title: Restraining Bolt
Gametext: Deploy on any droid at any site. Droid cannot move and cannot utilize its "game text." During your deploy phase, Restraining Bolt may be transferred (for free) to another droid at same site.

Title: Restricted Deployment
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. All opponent's warriors are deploy +1.

Title: Return Of A Jedi
Gametext: If Obi-Wan is lost, use 1 Force to retrieve him from the Lost Pile. OR Use 3 Force to search through your Reserve Deck and take Obi-Wan into your hand. Shuffle deck, cut and replace.

Title: Revolution
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on any location. Rotate the location so that icons and game texts switch direction. (If Expand the Empire present, it also switches.) If Revolution later canceled, location rotates back again.

Title: Rycar Ryjerd
Gametext: Deploy on your non-smuggler to give that character smuggler skill. OR Deploy on any smuggler. That character is power +1. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Sai'torr Kal Fas
Gametext: Deploy on your non-warrior character (except droids) to give that character warrior ([Warrior]) skill. OR Deploy on your warrior. That character is power +1. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Sandcrawler
Gametext: Deploys only to a Tatooine site. May add 1 driver and 7 passengers. Cannot move to mobile sites. Adds 1 to forfeit of each Jawa at same exterior site.

Title: Sandcrawler
Gametext: Deploys only to a Tatooine site. May add 1 driver and 7 passengers. Cannot move to mobile sites. Adds 1 to forfeit of each Jawa at same exterior site.

Title: Scanning Crew
Gametext: Use 1 Force to glance at the cards in the opponent's hand for 10 seconds. You may move any one Rebel you find there to the top of opponent's Used Pile.

Title: Scomp Link Access
Gametext: If one of your 'R' unit droids is at any Scomp link, you may: glance at the cards in any Reserve Deck for 20 seconds. Shuffle, cut and replace. OR If also at a Death Star site, cancel We're All Gonna Be A Lot Thinner or Boring Conversation Anyway.

Title: Send A Detachment Down
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Tatooine site (except docking bay). Target any trooper on Death Star. When target reaches Utinni Effect, attrition +1 against opponent in all Tatooine battles as long as target remains at same site as Utinni Effect.

Title: Sense
Gametext: Cancel one Interrupt (or one 'react') by drawing a destiny < ability of your highest-ability character on table. OR Cancel one Alter card just played.

Title: Sense
Gametext: Cancel one Interrupt (or one 'react') by drawing a destiny < ability of your highest-ability character on table. OR Cancel one Alter card just played.

Title: Set For Stun
Gametext: Use 2 Force to target one opponent's character. Draw destiny. If destiny > character's ability, character immediately returns to opponent's hand. (Also, any cards deployed on character return to owners' hands.)

Title: Shistavanen Wolfman
Gametext: May move to an adjacent site as a 'react'.

Title: Skywalkers
Gametext: If Luke and Leia are in a battle together, you may add two battle destiny. OR Cancel Imperial Barrier or Wrong Turn or Retract The Bridge.

Title: Solo Han
Gametext: If Han is defending a battle alone at a site, add two battle destiny. OR If any alien is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny.

Title: SoroSuub V-35 Landspeeder
Gametext: May add 1 driver and 3 passengers. Moves free if Owen Lars, Beru Lars or Luke aboard. May move as a 'react'.

Title: Spaceport Speeders
Gametext: Sell one of your vehicles or droids at Mos Eisley or same site as Wioslea. Draw two destiny (three destiny if vehicle is Luke's X-34 Landspeeder). The total is the 'offer,' which you must accept. Activate that much Force; then vehicle or droid is lost.

Title: Special Modifications
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any starship to add 2 to its armor or maneuver. If on Falcon with Han, Lando or Chewie piloting, also adds 2 to power and forfeit.

Title: Stormtrooper
Gametext: Deploys free to same site as one of your Imperials with ability > 2.

Title: Stormtrooper Backpack
Gametext: Deploy on your trooper. May use any number of weapons and devices. Trooper is immune to attrition < 3 when at a planet site.

Title: Stormtrooper Utility Belt
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any Imperial or alien. Character's power and forfeit are +1. If on Death Star, power and forfeit are +2.

Title: Sunsdown
Gametext: Deploy on any planet system to cause "nighttime conditions" at related sites. During battles there, both sides add one destiny to power only. Spies deploy free to sites under "nighttime conditions."

Title: Surprise Assault
Gametext: Use 1 Force to cancel a Force drain at one location. Draw one destiny for each character, starship and vehicle the opponent has present. Compare your destiny total to opponent's power total. Player with lowest total loses Force equal to the difference.

Title: Tactical Re-Call
Gametext: Deploy on any Yavin 4 site immediately after winning a battle elsewhere. Target a warrior involved in that battle. Target's power and forfeit are -2 (-3 if Leia) until target reaches this Utinni Effect (which is then canceled).

Title: Tagge Seeker
Gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Tagge (or warrior) of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an "all cards" situation). Seeker is also lost.

Title: Takeel
Gametext: If both players just drew one battle destiny, use 1 Force to switch numbers.

Title: Tallon Roll
Gametext: Target two starfighters (your TIE/ln and any Rebel starfighter) present at same system or sector. Each player draws destiny. Opponent totals destiny and starship's power. You total destiny, TIE's power and TIE's maneuver. Lowest total loses starfighter.

Title: Talz
Gametext: May forfeit in place of any other character hit by a weapon at same site, restoring that character to normal. Any Talz is power +2 under "nighttime conditions."

Title: Targeting Computer
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any starship. Adds 1 to starship's maneuver. If this starship is using a weapon during a battle, you may fire that weapon twice, separately or combined. Subtract 1 from each destiny draw when firing.

Title: Tarkin Seeker
Gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Tarkin (or alien) of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an "all cards" situation). Seeker is also lost.

Title: Tatooine
DarkSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.
LightSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.

Title: Tatooine
DarkSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.
LightSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.

Title: Tatooine Utility Belt
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any Rebel or alien. While on Tatooine, that character's power and forfeit are +2.

Title: Tatooine: Cantina
DarkSideText: Your aliens here, except Tusken Raiders, are each power +1.
LightSideText: Your aliens here are each forfeit +1.

Title: Tatooine: Cantina
DarkSideText: Your aliens here, except Tusken Raiders, are each forfeit +1.
LightSideText: Your aliens here are each power +1.

Title: Tatooine: Docking Bay 94
DarkSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
LightSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.

Title: Tatooine: Docking Bay 94
DarkSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.
LightSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.

Title: Tatooine: Dune Sea
DarkSideText: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.

Title: Tatooine: Jawa Camp
DarkSideText: Your Jawas deploy here for 1 Force from you only.
LightSideText: All your Jawas are power and forfeit -1 here.

Title: Tatooine: Jawa Camp
LightSideText: Your Jawas deploy here for 1 Force from you only, for free if Sandcrawler present.

Title: Tatooine: Jundland Wastes
DarkSideText: Your Tusken Raiders here are each forfeit +1. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
LightSideText: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.

Title: Tatooine: Lars' Moisture Farm
DarkSideText: Add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws here. If you control, Force drain +1 here.

Title: Tatooine: Lars' Moisture Farm
DarkSideText: Add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws here.
LightSideText: Beru Lars and Luke deploy -1 here.

Title: Tatooine: Mos Eisley
DarkSideText: Your spies, thieves, bounty hunters and smugglers are each power and forfeit +1 here.

Title: Tatooine: Mos Eisley
LightSideText: During your control phase, you may move free from here directly to Cantina (or vice versa).

Title: Tatooine: Obi-Wan's Hut
DarkSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.
LightSideText: Obi-Wan is deploy -3 here.

Title: Thank The Maker
Gametext: Use 1 Force during opponent's control phase if you have a droid on the table and were drained of at least 5 Force. Draw destiny. That number of cards are randomly selected and retrieved from your Lost Pile.

Title: The Bith Shuffle
Gametext: Shuffle any player's Reserve Deck or Lost Pile or Used Pile.

Title: The Circle Is Now Complete
Gametext: If Vader and Obi-Wan are present at same site, use 1 Force to initiate a duel between them. Compare their power, and add 2 if that character is armed with a lightsaber. Loser (lowest total) of duel is placed out of play.

Title: The Empire's Back
Gametext: If Vader, Tarkin, Motti or Tagge is lost, use 2 Force to retrieve one of them from the Lost Pile. OR Use 4 Force to search through your Reserve Deck and take Vader, Tarkin, Motti, or Tagge into your hand. Shuffle deck, cut and replace.

Title: The Force Is Strong With This One
Gametext: If Luke and an Imperial with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle, you may add one battle destiny (add two destiny if Imperial is Vader).

Title: This Is All Your Fault
Gametext: Lose a droid to cancel all attrition against you at same site this turn. OR Re-target an opponent's weapon to one of your droids at same site as target. If droid is 'hit', use original target's forfeit number.

Title: TIE Advanced x1
Gametext: Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: TIE Fighter
Gametext: Deploy -1 to same system as any Imperial capital starship. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: TIE Scout
Gametext: May add 1 Pilot and 1 passenger, or 2 passengers. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Timer Mine
Gametext: Deploy on opponent's side at same site as one of your mining droids. 'Explodes' at beginning of your next turn. Draw destiny. That number of opponent's characters there are immediately lost (owner's choice). Timer Mine is also lost.

Title: Timer Mine
Gametext: Deploy on opponent's side at same site as one of your mining droids. 'Explodes' at beginning of your next turn. Draw destiny. That number of opponent's characters there are immediately lost (owner's choice). Timer Mine is also lost.

Title: Tonnika Sisters
Gametext: Twice during each of your control phases, may use 2 Force to draw 2 destiny for 2 chances at a destiny = 2. If successful, may steal or destroy up to 2 weapons or 2 devices present.

Title: Traffic Control
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your side of table. During your control phase, you may return any cards from your hand to the top of your Used Pile.

Title: Trinto Duaba
Gametext: If there are cards in the opponent's Used Pile during your battle phase, draw one destiny. All cards there with the same destiny number are lost.

Title: Trooper Charge
Gametext: Select one of your troopers in a battle to make a 'charge.' If that trooper is a Death Star Trooper, it is power +3 the battle. If any other trooper, power +2. However, that trooper must be forfeited at end of battle.

Title: Turbolaser Battery
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer or any mobile system. May target a starship using 2 Force. Draw two destiny. Subtract 2 if targeting a capital starship. Otherwise, subtract 5. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.

Title: Tusken Breath Mask
Gametext: Deploy on any Tatooine site where you have just won a battle. Target one of your characters not at Tatooine. Upon reaching, target takes mask. While on Tatooine, target's power and forfeit are +2 and has immunity to attrition of exactly 3.

Title: Tusken Raider
Gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power + 1 if another non-unique Tusken Raider present. If you have four or more non-unique Tusken Raiders present, your total power here is +2.

Title: Tusken Scavengers
Gametext: Use 1 Force to draw destiny. If destiny < the number of Tusken Raiders on table, you may scavenge (search through) the opponent's Used Pile. All vehicles, weapons or devices you find there are lost.

Title: Ubrikkian 9000 Z001
Gametext: May add 1 driver and 2 passengers. May move as a 'react.'

Title: Utinni!
Gametext: If one of your Jawas is at the same location as any Utinni Effect, 'steal' that Utinni Effect into your hand, to use or lose as your own. OR Cancel any Interrupt or Effect with 'Jawa' in the card name.

Title: Utinni!
Gametext: If one of your Jawas is at the same location as any Utinni Effect, 'steal' that Utinni Effect into your hand, to use or lose as your own. OR Cancel any Interrupt or Effect with 'Jawa' in the card name.

Title: Vader's Custom TIE
Gametext: May add 1 pilot. If Vader is pilot, Custom TIE is immune to attrition < 4.

Title: Vader's Eye
Gametext: If Vader is defending a battle alone at a site, add 1 to power and add one battle destiny. OR If any other Imperial with ability > 2 is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny.

Title: Vader's Lightsaber
Gametext: Deploy on Vader. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.

Title: Vaporator
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on any Tatooine site. Cannot be moved. Protects all characters at same site, or an adjacent site, from Gravel Storm.

Title: Warrior's Courage
Gametext: If any warrior is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny. OR If Leia is defending a battle alone at a site, add two battle destiny.

Title: We're All Gonna Be A Lot Thinner!
Gametext: Everything in Trash Compactor is crushed (Lost).

Title: We're Doomed
Gametext: If you have less than 15 Life Force, play during opponent's control phase. For remainder of turn, each time you must lose Force, the loss is cut in half (round up). If R2-D2 or C-3PO on table, round down.

Title: WED15-I662 'Treadwell' Droid
Gametext: Adds immunity to attrition < 2 to all your vehicles and droids at same location. Also, if 'treadwell' droid is at a docking bay, adds immunity to attrition < 3 to all your starfighters at the related system and related sectors.

Title: WED-9-M1 'Bantha' Droid
Gametext: Adds immunity to attrition < 2 to all your vehicles and droids at same location. Also, if 'bantha' droid is at a docking bay, adds immunity to attrition < 3 to all your starfighters at the related system and related sectors and may cancel Lateral Damage.

Title: Wioslea
Gametext: During your control phase, may use 1 Force to target an opponent's unoccupied transport vehicle or droid present. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's destiny number, use Force equal to target's deploy cost to 'purchase' target (use as if stolen).

Title: Wrong Turn
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. All opponent's warriors are deploy +1.

Title: Wuher
Gametext: If at the beginning of your control phase any weapons or droids are present at same site, all of them are lost. If in the Cantina, all weapons and droids there are immediately lost.

Title: X-wing
Gametext: Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Yavin 4
DarkSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.
LightSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.

Title: Yavin 4
DarkSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.
LightSideText: If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.

Title: Yavin 4: Docking Bay
DarkSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
LightSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.

Title: Yavin 4: Docking Bay
DarkSideText: Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.
LightSideText: Your docking bay transit from here is free.

Title: Yavin 4: Jungle
DarkSideText: An Imperial alone here battles at power +2 and is immune to attrition.

Title: Yavin 4: Jungle
DarkSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.
LightSideText: A Rebel alone here battles at power +2 and is immune to attrition.

Title: Yavin 4: Massassi Throne Room
DarkSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.
LightSideText: If this is your starting location, Light Side goes first in game.

Title: Yavin 4: Massassi War Room
DarkSideText: If you initiate a battle here, add one battle destiny.
LightSideText: If you control, with a leader here, all Stormtroopers and TIEs on table are forfeit -1.

Title: Yavin Sentry
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy at any Yavin 4 site. Declare one of the following to affect that site and adjacent sites while 'sentry' present: Opponent's deploy +1. OR Opponent's ability required for battle destiny +1. OR Your total power +1.

Title: Yerka Mig
Gametext: Deploy at any location. You may move Mig like a character. Target an opponent's character, who may apprehend (cancel) Mig by reaching same location. Until then, during all battles at same and adjacent sites to Mig, opponent's total power is -1.

Title: You Overestimate Their Chances
Gametext: If an opponent has just initiated a battle, triple the resulting battle damage for the eventual loser. OR Triple the result of Don't Underestimate Our Chances.

Title: Your Eyes Can Deceive You
Gametext: Deploy beside either player's Lost Pile. That pile is turned face down. Cards from that player's Life Force may not be viewed when they are lost.

Title: Your Powers Are Weak, Old Man
Gametext: During any battle involving both Vader and Obi-Wan, you may add one battle destiny. OR Destroy (cancel) either: Return Of A Jedi, Jedi Lightsaber, Jedi Presence or Old Ben.

Title: Y-wing
Gametext: May add 1 pilot or passenger. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Gold Leader In Gold 1
Gametext: May add 1 pilot or passenger. Permanent pilot aboard is •Dutch, who provides ability of 2, adds 2 to power and may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: Red Leader In Red 1
Gametext: Permanent pilot aboard is •Red Leader, who provides ability of 2, adds 2 to power and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: 3B3-10
Gametext: While at Theed Palace Hallway, opponent's characters may not move from here. Once per game may take Halt! into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: 3B3-1204
Gametext: While with two other battle droids, may use 1 Force to target an opponent's Jedi present. Target's immunity to attrition is canceled for remainder of turn.

Title: 3B3-21
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle at same site, may use X Force to reveal the top X cards of your Reserve Deck (maximum 4). Any battle droids revealed this way may deploy for free; all other cards are lost.

Title: 3B3-888
Gametext: Once per turn may use 1 Force to target an opponent's character present; target is defense value -3 for remainder of turn. While with another battle droid at a site, draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise.

Title: AAT Assault Leader
Gametext: May add 1 pilot and 3 passengers. While piloted at same site as another AAT, adds two battle destiny. During your deploy phase, may deploy one Energy Shell Launchers aboard from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 5.

Title: AAT Laser Cannon
Gametext: Deploy on your AAT. May target a character (use 1 Force) or vehicle (for free) at same or adjacent site. Draw destiny. Character lost if destiny +1 > defense value. Vehicle lost if destiny +3 > defense value. May target a creature for free. Creature is lost.

Title: Activate The Droids
Gametext: Deploy on your Blockade Flagship (may not deploy on a site). Whenever you initiate battle at a related planet site where you have a battle droid, you may activate 2 Force or retrieve 1 Force.

Title: After Her!
Gametext: If opponent just Force drained you at a location, deploy on that location. Opponent's Force drains here are +1. Your battle destiny draws here are +1. If you control this location, may place Immediate Effect in Used Pile to retrieve 4 Force. (Immune to Control.)

Title: Amidala's Blaster
Gametext: Deploy on Amidala. May target a character or creature for free. Draw destiny. Character is power and forfeit = 0 if destiny > defense value. Creature lost if destiny +2 > defense value.

Title: Armored Attack Tank
Gametext: May add 1 pilot and 3 passengers. While piloted at same site as a battle droid, adds two battle destiny. Landspeed may not be increased. Immune to attrition < 4.

Title: Artoo, Brave Little Droid
Gametext: While aboard any starfighter, adds 2 to its power and hyperspeed. While in battle at a system, may place Artoo in Used Pile to cancel a just-drawn battle destiny. Cancels Lateral Damage targeting a starship at same system.

Title: Artoo, Brave Little Droid
Gametext: While aboard any starfighter, adds 2 to its power and hyperspeed. While in battle at a system, may place Artoo in Used Pile to cancel a just-drawn battle destiny. Cancels Lateral Damage targeting a starship at same system.

Title: Ascension Guns
Gametext: During your move phase, target any number of your characters at Theed Palace Hallway. Draw destiny. If destiny +2 > number of characters targeted, relocate those characters to one other interior Naboo site. Otherwise, targets are lost.

Title: At Last We Are Getting Results
Gametext: Deploy on table. Your [Trade Federation] starfighters are forfeit +2. During every draw phase, opponent loses 1 Force unless they occupy a battleground system. Effect lost if you do not occupy two battleground systems with [Trade Federation] starships.

Title: Battle Droid Officer
Gametext: Your infantry battle droids deploy -1 to same site. While with another battle droid, adds 1 to your total battle destiny here. Your battle droids may move to this site for free.

Title: Battle Droid Pilot
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 while piloting a battleship). While piloting a battleship draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise.

Title: Big Boomers!
Gametext: If there is more than 1 card in opponent's Force Pile, opponent must use 1 Force. OR Take a Fambaa or Booma into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR If you just drew weapon destiny for your Booma, cancel that destiny to cause a re-draw.

Title: Blockade Flagship
Gametext: May add 4 pilots, 4 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 droid starfighters. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Once per game, may deploy a Neimoidian pilot aboard from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Blockade Flagship: Docking Bay
DarkSideText: Your Docking Bay transit from here is free.
LightSideText: Your Docking Bay transit to and from here requires +8 Force.

Title: Blockade Flagship: Docking Bay
DarkSideText: Your Docking Bay transit from here requires 1 Force. If just "blown away", lose 4 Force.
LightSideText: This site may not be converted.

Title: Bok Askol
Gametext: Once during your deploy phase, may draw destiny: (0-2) no result; (3-4) Askol draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise for remainder of turn; (5+) Askol is power +4 for remainder of turn.

Title: Booma
Gametext: Deploy on your Fambaa. Twice during battle may draw destiny. If destiny < total number of opponent's characters and vehicles present, one of them is lost (opponent's choice).

Title: Boss Nass
Gametext: While at an underwater site and all of your characters on Naboo are Gungans: add one battle destiny in battles at Naboo sites and once during your deploy phase may deploy a Gungan or Steady, Steady from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Boss Nass
Gametext: While at an underwater site and all of your characters on Naboo are Gungans: add one battle destiny in battles at Naboo sites and once during your deploy phase may deploy a Gungan or Steady, Steady from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Bravo 1
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. May add 1 pilot. While Ric piloting, immune to attrition < 4 and draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise.

Title: Bravo 2
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. May add 1 pilot. While Dolphe piloting, immune to attrition < 4. While at Naboo system, your Bravo Squadron pilots at same system are forfeit +2.

Title: Bravo 3
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. May add 1 pilot. While Arven piloting, immune to attrition < 4. While at Naboo system, opponent's battle destiny draws are -1 here.

Title: Bravo 4
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. May add 1 pilot. While Rya piloting, immune to attrition < 4. While at Naboo system, adds 1 to each of your Force drains there.

Title: Bravo 5
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. May add 1 pilot. While Ellberger piloting, immune to attrition < 3. While at Naboo, opponent's battleships present are power -1.

Title: Bravo Fighter
Gametext: Permanent pilot provides ability of 3. During your control phase, if landed aboard Blockade Flagship, may draw one destiny. If destiny > 6, place Bravo Fighter in your Used Pile; Flagship 'blown away.'

Title: Captain Daultay Dofine
Gametext: Adds 3 to power of any capital starship he pilots. Once per game may take Activate The Droids into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While aboard Blockade Flagship, it is immune to attrition < 5 and Activate The Droids is immune to Alter.

Title: Captain Tarpals
Gametext: Adds 1 to power of your other Gungans at same site. Opponent's characters may not move to underwater sites. Once per turn, if you just drew a Gungan for battle destiny, may deploy that Gungan for free to cancel that destiny and re-draw.

Title: Captain Tarpals' Electropole
Gametext: Deploys on Captain Tarpals. May 'throw' (place in Used Pile) to target a character, creature or vehicle for free. Draw destiny. If destiny +3 > defense value, target is landspeed = 0 and power -3 for remainder of turn.

Title: Cease Fire!
Gametext: If a battle was just initiated, lose 2 Force to prevent all weapons from being fired for remainder of battle. OR Target all your battle droids at a site. Targets may not have their forfeit value reduced for remainder of turn. OR Cancel Blaster Proficiency.

Title: Corporal Rushing
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. While firing a blaster, adds one to total weapon destiny. Once per battle, if a battle droid was just hit by a blaster here, battle droid is lost and opponent loses 1 Force.

Title: Dams Denna
Gametext: Once during your deploy phase, you may deploy a Kaadu, Fambaa or Eopie to same site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If you just lost a creature vehicle from same site, you may place that creature vehicle in your Used Pile.

Title: Darth Maul With Lightsaber
Gametext: Permanent weapon is •Maul's Double-Bladed Lightsaber (twice per battle, may target a character for free; draw two destiny; target 'hit', and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value).

Title: Darth Sidious
Gametext: While no other characters present, if opponent just lost a Jedi from table, may lose 1 Force to place that Jedi out of play. While on Coruscant, may use 1 Force to add one battle destiny in a battle your Neimoidian is in. Immune to attrition.

Title: Darth Sidious
Gametext: While no other characters present, if opponent just lost a Jedi from table, may lose 1 Force to place that Jedi out of play. While on Coruscant, may use 1 Force to add one battle destiny in a battle your Neimoidian is in. Immune to attrition.

Title: DFS Squadron Starfighter
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo or same system as your battleship. While at same system as your battleship, during your deploy phase, may deploy one Droid Starfighter Laser Cannons aboard from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: DFS-1015
Gametext: Deploys -1 to same location as your battleship. While with another droid starfighter at a system, once per battle if about to draw a battle destiny here, may instead draw two and choose one.

Title: DFS-1308
Gametext: Deploys -1 to same location as your battleship. While with another droid starfighter at a system, opponent may not draw more than one battle destiny here.

Title: DFS-327
Gametext: While at same system as your battleship, DFS-327 is power +3, and opponent's pilots deploy +2 to starfighters at this system.

Title: Droid Racks
Gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on table. If your battle droid was just lost, may place it here. During your control phase, may use 2 Force (1 Force if your piloted MTT on table) to take any battle droid from here into hand. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Droid Starfighter Laser Cannons
Gametext: Deploy on your droid starfighter. May target a starship using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value. If destiny +1 = defense value, target is power = 0 until end of turn.

Title: Drop Your Weapons
Gametext: Target an opponent's weapon at same site as your battle droid. Each of that weapon's destiny draws are -1 for remainder of turn. OR If your battle droid just fired a blaster and hit a character, all opponent's character weapons at same site are lost.

Title: Electropole
Gametext: Deploy on your Gungan. May target a character for free. Draw destiny. If destiny > defense value, character is power -4 for remainder of turn. At the end of a battle here, may place this electropole on top of Reserve Deck.

Title: Energy Shell Launchers
Gametext: Deploy on your AAT. May target a character or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. May subtract 1. If destiny = target's destiny number, target is hit.

Title: Fambaa
Gametext: May add 2 'riders' (passengers). Ability = ½. Requires +1 force to use landspeed. May not be attacked by creatures.

Title: Fighters Straight Ahead
Gametext: Deploy on table. Your Force generation is +1 at systems you control. Opponent's non-unique starfighters are deploy +1 (or +2 to a system you occupy). (Immune to Alter.)

Title: General Jar Jar
Gametext: Once per game may take Brisky Morning Munchen into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once per battle, may use 1 Force to target an opponent's droid present. Both players draw destiny. If your destiny +1 > opponent's destiny, target lost.

Title: General Jar Jar
Gametext: Once per game may take Brisky Morning Munchen into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once per battle, may use 1 Force to target an opponent's droid present. Both players draw destiny. If your destiny +1 > opponent's destiny, target lost.

Title: Get To Your Ships!
Gametext: Deploy on table. Once during your deploy phase, may reveal an unpiloted starfighter from hand to take its matching pilot character from Reserve Deck (or vice versa) and deploy both simultaneously; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Gian Speeder
Gametext: May add 1 driver and 3 passengers. May move as a 'react' to Naboo sites. Your battle destiny draws at same site are +1 for each of your Royal Naboo Security present. (Limit +3.)

Title: Gimme A Lift!
Gametext: Relocate Jar Jar to a battle just initiated at an adjacent site. OR Increase Jar Jar's landspeed by 1 for remainder of turn. OR If Jar Jar on Brisky Morning Munchen, take him into hand.

Title: Gungan Energy Shield
Gametext: Deploy on an exterior site. While your Fambaa here: your characters here may not be targeted by weapons, opponent's battle destiny draws here are -1, and characters must use +1 Force when moving to or from here using their landspeed.

Title: Gungan General
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. Your Gungans at same site are forfeit +2. While in a battle, if you just drew a Gungan for battle destiny you may take that card into hand.

Title: Gungan Guard
Gametext: Your Gungan leaders present may not be targeted by weapons. While defending a battle on Naboo, power +4 and, whenever you draw a Gungan for battle destiny, add 3 to that destiny. Requires +2 Force to use landspeed.

Title: Halt!
Gametext: During any deploy phase, target a character at same site as your battle droid. Target is landspeed = 0 for remainder of turn. OR If opponent just deployed a character to same site as your battle droid, opponent must use 1 Force or place that character in hand.

Title: I'll Try Spinning
Gametext: Landed starfighters and vehicles aboard starships are forfeit = 0. Once during your control phase may target your N-1 starfighter and opponent's starfighter present at same system. Both players draw destiny. You add your starfighter's power and maneuver. Opponent adds starfighter's power. Starship with lowest total is lost.

Title: Infantry Battle Droid
Gametext: Power +1 in battles you initiate. Once per turn, if this droid just fired a blaster and 'hit' an opponent's character, opponent loses 1 Force. Opponent's Gungans and Republic characters present are forfeit -1.

Title: Invasion
Gametext:
While this side up, you lose no more than 2 Force to any Force drain. Your battle droids deploy -1. If you have two [Presence] droids with different card titles (or a [Presence] droid and a Neimoidian) in battle at a site, draw two battle destiny if unable to otherwise. Your droid starfighters are immune to attrition < 3. If opponent just drew an Interrupt for battle destiny, once per battle you may place that card out of play.
Flip this card if opponent controls Naboo system or Theed Palace Throne Room.

Title: In Complete Control
Gametext:
Deploy Naboo system with Blockade Flagship there, Naboo: Swamp, and Droid Racks.
For remainder of game, you may not deploy cards with ability except [Trade Federation] starships and characters with 'Trade Federation' in lore. Civil Disorder is canceled.
While this side up, once during your deploy phase may deploy a Naboo site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent's Force icons at Naboo system are canceled.
Flip this card if you control Theed Palace Throne Room (with a Neimoidian there) and Naboo system.

Title: It's On Automatic Pilot!
Gametext: Deploy on table. Your N-1 starfighters are forfeit +2. During every draw phase, opponent loses 1 Force unless they occupy a battleground system. Effect lost if you do not occupy two battleground systems with [Republic] starships.

Title: Jerus Jannick
Gametext: Deploys -2 to same site as Amidala. While in a battle with Amidala or Leia, your leaders present may not be targeted by weapons, and Jerus may be forfeited to satisfy all battle damage and attrition against you.

Title: Kaadu
Gametext: May add 1 'rider' (passenger). Ability = ½. Moves for free. While 'ridden' by a Gungan, may move as a 'react'. While at a swamp, adds 1 to your Force drains there.

Title: Let's Go Left
Gametext: Non-pilot characters aboard starships are forfeit -4. Whenever a player's starship is 'hit', that player loses 1 Force (2 if starship was 'hit' by Proton Torpedoes.) At systems where you have only [Republic] starships, all of those starships are immune to attrition < 4. At sites related to a system you occupy, your battle destinies may not be canceled by opponent.

Title: Lieutenant Arven Wendik
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While piloting Bravo 3 at same system as a battleship, adds one destiny to attrition only.

Title: Lieutenant Chamberlyn
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Naboo. Once per game may deploy a blaster on Chamberlyn from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once during your control phase, may target a battle droid present and draw destiny. If destiny > 3, target lost.

Title: Lieutenant Rya Kirsch
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While piloting Bravo 4, draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise, and opponent's droid starfighters are deploy +2 to same system.

Title: Mace Windu, Jedi Master
