Gametext: Deploys only aboard Executor or on any Death Star Site. Cannot move. May cancel opponent's Force Drains at adjacent Death Star or Executor sites.

Title: Impressive, Most Impressive
Gametext: If opponent just attempted to 'freeze' a character using Carbon-Freezing or All Too Easy, draw destiny. Add character's ability. If total destiny > 7, effect canceled. Character released (if captive) and 'hides' (may not participate in battle) for remainder of turn.

Title: Innocent Scoundrel
Gametext: USED: If your gambler was just targeted by a weapon, opponent must choose to select a new target or lose 2 Force. LOST: Cancel any Effect (except those immune to Alter) deployed on Han or your Lando.

Title: Interrogation Array
Gametext: Deploy on a prison. During your control phase, opponent loses 1 Force for each captive of ability > 2 here. Also, during your control phase, may use 1 Force to search your Reserve Deck, take one Torture or Aiiii! Aaa! Agggggggggg! into hand and reshuffle.

Title: Into The Ventilation Shaft, Lefty
Gametext: Relocate one of your characters from a Cloud City site to Weather Vane (if 'hit', character is fi rst restored to normal). May be played even after a battle has just been initiated.

Title: It's A Trap!
Gametext: USED: Cancel Sniper or Blasted Droid. LOST: Use 3 Force to cancel any battle just initiated at a site. (Immune to Sense.)

Title: Kebyc
Gametext: When at a site and opponent is losing Force from Force drains at cloud sectors on same planet, lost force must come from Reserve Deck, if possible.

Title: Keep Your Eyes Open
Gametext: If a battle was just initiated where you have two smugglers, you may move any or all of your characters, vehicles and starships away (at normal use of the Force). OR Glance at the cards in any Lost Pile and replace unshuffled.

Title: Lando Calrissian
Gametext: Deploys only on Cloud City. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When playing Sabacc, may subtract 1 from or add 1 to your total. If present at a site, can be replaced by opponent with any Light Side Lando.

Title: Lando Calrissian
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if piloting Falcon). Power +1 for every Cloud City location you control. When playing Sabacc, may add 1 to or subtract 1 from your total.

Title: Lando's Wrist Comlink
Gametext: Deploy on a character. When at a Cloud City site, Lobot and your Cloud City troopers may deploy or move here as a 'react.'

Title: Leia Of Alderaan
Gametext: Deploy on Leia. While at any Rebel Base site, your Rebels, except unique (•) Rebels, are deploy -2 and power +2 at same and adjacent sites. While at any system, your starfighters, except unique (•) starfighters, are deploy -2 there.

Title: Levitation Attack
Gametext: If a battle was just initiated where you have a character of ability > 3 present, search your Used Pile for one device which deploys on a character. Add device's destiny number to your total power, then place device on top of your Used Pile.

Title: Lieutenant Cecius
Gametext: Deploys free to any Executor site. Power +3 when participating in a Besieged battle. During your control phase, may use 1 Force to search your Reserve Deck, take one Besieged or Set For Stun into hand and reshuffle.

Title: Lieutenant Sheckil
Gametext: During your control phase, may use 1 Force to search your Reserve Deck, take one Human Shield into hand and reshuffle. When escorting a captive, captive is forfeit +2 and Sheckil is immune to attrition < 4.

Title: Lift Tube Escape
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle, one of your Lift Tubes present may move as a 'react' from that battle. OR Place one of your unoccupied Lift Tubes on table in your Used Pile. OR Search your Reserve Deck, take one Lift Tube into hand and reshuffle.

Title: Lobot
Gametext: Deploys only as a 'react' to a Cloud City site or to where your Lando is present. When present at a Scomp link, power +2 and opponent's total power is -2 at same site. Your Cloud City troopers deploy free and are power +1 at same Cloud City site.

Title: Luke's Blaster Pistol
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on Luke, 3 on your other warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 2 Force. (If targeted by Luke, target loses any immunity to attrition for remainder of turn.) Draw destiny. Add 1 if targeting a character or creature. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.

Title: Mandalorian Armor
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on any alien or Imperial (except Vader or Boba Fett). Character is power +2, has armor = 5 and is immune to attrition < 3.

Title: Mostly Armless
Gametext: If your character with a lightsaber just won a battle, deploy on an opponent's character present. Character is Disarmed (power -1 and may no longer carry weapons). Opponent loses 1 Force at the end of each of opponent's turns. (Immune to Control.)

Title: NOOOOOOOOOOOO!
Gametext: USED: If you just answered 'no' to a Hypo question, opponent loses 3 Force. LOST: Cancel Why Didn't You Tell Me? or I Am Your Father. OR If Luke is about to cross to the Dark Side, he is lost instead.

Title: Obsidian 7
Gametext: Deploy -1 and power +3 at any cloud sector. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 2.

Title: Obsidian 8
Gametext: Deploy -1 and power +3 at any cloud sector. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Off The Edge
Gametext: Target one of your characters at a Cloud City site. Draw destiny. If destiny > character's destiny number, retrieve Force equal to the difference. If destiny < character's destiny number, lose difference. If destiny = character's destiny number, character is lost.

Title: Old Pirates
Gametext: If a battle was just initiated involving Han and any Lando, the eventual loser of the battle may not lose cards from Life Force to satisfy battle damage while that player has any cards in hand. OR Cancel Double-Crossing, No-Good Swindler.

Title: Out Of Somewhere
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle with more than double your total power, search your Reserve Deck. Any one character you find there may deploy as a 'react' (at normal use of the Force). Reshuffle.

Title: Path Of Least Resistance
Gametext: Cancel Rite Of Passage. OR Relocate one of your characters at an interior mobile site to a related interior mobile site.

Title: Point Man
Gametext: Cancel Demotion, Restricted Deployment, Commence Recharging, Logistical Delay, They're On Dantooine, Asteroid Sanctuary, Scramble, Order To Engage, No Disintegrations, Asteroids Do Not Concern Me, Report To Lord Vader or What Is Thy Bidding, My Master?

Title: Prepare The Chamber
Gametext: USED: Add 2 to Carbon Freezing destiny. LOST: If one of your Ugnaughts is defending in a battle, add one battle destiny.

Title: Princess Leia
Gametext: Deploys only on Hoth or Cloud City. Adds 1 to power of anything she pilots. May deploy (on Hoth or Cloud City) or move as a 'react' to same site as Han or Luke. Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: Projective Telepathy
Gametext: Cancel Anger, Fear, Aggression when it is inserted or revealed. OR If your opponent just initiated a battle or Force drain, opponent must choose to use 2 Force, or cancel that battle or Force drain.

Title: Protector
Gametext: If Leia and Chewie are in a battle together, you may add two battle destiny. OR If Leia is participating in a battle, you may lose Chewie from hand to satisfy all battle damage and attrition against you. OR Cancel I'd Just As Soon Kiss A Wookiee or Frustration.

Title: Punch It!
Gametext: If Han or your Lando is piloting a starfighter which is defending a battle at a system, add one battle destiny (add two if starfighter is Falcon). Also, starfighter is immune to attrition for remainder of turn.

Title: Put That Down
Gametext: If one of your characters was just targeted by a weapon during battle, use 3 Force to cancel that targeting. OR Cancel Double Back or Res Luk Ra'auf.

Title: Redemption
Gametext: May add 4 pilots and 4 passengers. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Your medical droids and Bacta Tank 'patients' may deploy aboard for free.

Title: Release Your Anger
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle, you may do one of the following: Add one destiny to your total power only. OR If you have a character weapon present, select one opponent's character present to lose all immunity to attrition for remainder of battle.

Title: Rendezvous Point On Tatooine
Gametext: During your control phase, use 1 Force to move any one of your [Cloud City] characters of ability > 1 to any [Jabba's Palace] location where you have presence. If moving to any Jabba's Palace site, this movement is free and you do not need presence.

Title: Rescue In The Clouds
Gametext: USED: If you have a character on Weather Vane, place that character on your Used Pile. LOST: Deploy one or more vehicles, starfighters and pilots (at normal use of the Force) as a 'react' to a cloud sector.

Title: Restricted Access
Gametext: Insert face up in your Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost, along with all opponent's 'insert' cards there. Reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.) OR Deploy between two mobile sites. Opponent's characters may pass only if aboard a Lift Tube or opponent uses +1 Force each.

Title: Rite Of Passage
Gametext: At the beginning of opponent's move phase, target an opponent's character alone at a mobile site and select an adjacent site. Opponent must choose to move target there for free (target cannot move for remainder of turn), lose target or lose 2 Force.

Title: Shattered Hope
Gametext: If a battle you won just ended at an interior site and you have a character of ability > 3 present there, relocate one opponent's character present to an adjacent site. (If on Cloud City, may relocate that character to Weather Vane instead.)

Title: Shocking Information
Gametext: Target a location. Scomp links there cannot be used for remainder of turn. OR If opponent is about to scan or otherwise look through your hand (unless using Monnok), opponent continues but must lose 4 Force plus the card allowing the scan.

Title: Shocking Revelation
Gametext: Target a location. Scomp links there cannot be used for remainder of turn. OR If opponent is about to scan or otherwise look through your hand (unless using Grimtaash), opponent continues but must lose 4 Force plus the card allowing the scan.

Title: Slave I
Gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a bounty hunter) and 3 passengers. May deploy with a pilot as a 'react'. Immune to attrition < 5 if Boba Fett piloting. Has ship-docking capability.

Title: Slip Sliding Away
Gametext: Relocate a card from the top of any Deck or Pile to the bottom (without looking). OR If you have a droid at a Scomp link on Cloud City, cancel Into The Ventilation Shaft, Lefty. OR Use 3 Force to cause a character at Weather vane to be lost.

Title: Smoke Screen
Gametext: During a battle at a site, if you are about to draw a card for battle destiny, you may instead use the ability number of one of your characters involved in the battle.

Title: Somersault
Gametext: During a battle at a site, just before drawing battle destiny, if opponent has less than double your total power, use 4 Force to switch your total power with opponent's. OR If both players just drew one battle destiny, use 1 Force to switch numbers.

Title: Sonic Bombardment
Gametext: USED: Search your Reserve Deck, take any one prison into hand and reshuffle. LOST: If you have an opponent's alien captive at a prison, opponent loses 3 Force.

Title: Special Delivery
Gametext: Deploy on a prison. When one of your troopers 'delivers' (imprisons) a captive here, you may search your Lost Pile, take any one card into hand and then lose this Effect (each captive may be 'delivered' only once until they are released or leave table).

Title: Surprise
Gametext: Use 3 Force: Retarget an Interrupt or Utinni Effect which specifies a target to another appropriate target on the same side of the Force. OR Relocate any Effect (except those immune to Alter) deployed on a location to another appropriate location.

Title: Surreptitious Glance
Gametext: If Lobot and your Lando are in a battle together, cancel one opponent's destiny draw immediately after it is revealed. OR use 4 Force to cancel Dark Deal.

Title: Swing-And-A-Miss
Gametext: If opponent just used a lightsaber to target, draw one destiny and subtract that amount from opponent's weapon destiny. OR Cancel one Mostly Armless card just played. OR Cancel Dark Strike, End This Destructive Conflict or Focused Attack.

Title: The Emperor's Prize
Gametext: If Luke was just 'frozen,' deploy on Emperor or Detention Block Corridor. Target Luke and Vader. When reached by targets, place Utinni Effect on Luke and opponent must lose half of Life Force (round down). If Luke released, lose Utinni Effect. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: This Is Even Better
Gametext: If Han and Leia are together in a battle you just lost, forfeit one of them to satisfy all battle damage and attrition against you. OR If Han is a captive and a battle was just initiated where you have Leia (or vice versa), add one battle destiny. OR Cancel This Is Still Wrong.

Title: This Is Still Wrong
Gametext: If a battle was just initiated where opponent has a female targeted by This Is Just Wrong, add one battle destiny. OR Search your Reserve Deck, take one This Is Just Wrong into hand and reshuffle. OR Cancel This Is More Like It.

Title: Tibanna Gas Miner
Gametext: When at a site, adds 1 to your Force drains at related cloud sectors. Also, during your activate phase, if at a Cloud City site and you control Bespin: Cloud City, may cumulatively activate 1 Force for every cloud sector on Bespin.

Title: Tibanna Gas Miner
Gametext: When at a site, adds 1 to your Force drains at related cloud sectors. Also, during your activate phase, if at a Cloud City site and you control Bespin: Cloud City, may cumulatively activate 1 Force for every cloud sector on Bespin.

Title: TIE Sentry Ships
Gametext: If opponent just initiated a Force drain at a system, cloud sector or asteroid sector, you may 'react' by deploying TIEs and pilots to that location (at normal use of the Force).

Title: Treva Horme
Gametext: During your control phase, may 'sell' one Interrupt card from hand. Opponent must use X Force, where X = destiny of that card or entire Force Pile (opponent's choice). Place sold card on opponent's Used Pile and activate X Force.

Title: Trooper Assault
Gametext: If a battle was just initiated at a site, each of your troopers present is power +2 and immune to attrition for remainder of turn.

Title: Trooper Jerrol Blendin
Gametext: Deploys only on Cloud City, but may move elsewhere. Power +2 when participating in a battle you initiate. Opponent may use 2 Force to 'bribe' (exclude) Blendin from battle.

Title: Trooper Utris M'Toc
Gametext: Deploys only on Cloud City, but may move elsewhere. Deploys free to same Cloud City site as Lando. Power +2 when defending a battle. Your other Cloud City troopers are forfeit +2 where present.

Title: Ugloste
Gametext: Power +2 at Trash Compactor, Droid Junkheap, Incinerator or Carbonite Chamber. Functions as a leader if present with another Ugnaught. Where present, other Ugnaughts are forfeit +2 and double their bonus to Carbon-Freezing destiny.

Title: Ugnaught
Gametext: When at Carbonite Chamber, cumulatively adds 1 to each Carbon-Freezing destiny draw. During your control phase, may lose 1 Force from hand to search your Lost Pile and take one weapon or device into hand.

Title: Uncontrollable Fury
Gametext: Deploy on Vader. He is power +2, but neither adds 1 to battle destiny nor allows Tarkin to cancel destiny. Opponent loses 2 Force at end of each of opponent's turns in which Vader did not battle and you had a character of ability > 3 on table. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Vader's Bounty
Gametext: Deploy on a Rebel of ability > 2. If subsequently captured by a bounty hunter and then transferred to a prison where Vader is present, retrieve Force equal to character's forfeit (+4 if Luke) and lose Effect. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Vader's Cape
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on one of your Imperials or aliens. Immune to attrition < 5. When in battle, adds 1 to each of your battle destiny draws.

Title: We'll Find Han
Gametext: Deploy Han to same site as Chewie or your Lando (regardless of location deployment restrictions). OR If Chewie and your Lando are in a battle together, subtract 3 from attrition against you (cannot fall below zero). OR Cancel I Had No Choice.

Title: We're The Bait
Gametext: Deploy on Han, Leia or Chewie if captured or 'frozen.' Target Luke. Luke may not attempt Jedi Tests. Also, during each of opponent's draw phases, opponent loses 2 Force (3 if captive is 'frozen'). Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Weapon Levitation
Gametext: USED: Search your Used Pile, take one weapon into hand and reshuffle. LOST: If a battle was just initiated, one of your characters of ability > 3 present may 'steal' one character weapon present.

Title: Weapon Of An Ungrateful Son
Gametext: USED: If a lightsaber was just used to enhance a Force drain, place it in owner's Used Pile. LOST: Place any or all of your devices and character weapons on table in your Used Pile.

Title: Weather Vane
Gametext: Deploy on table. Any character here may be captured or rescued by a player's starship or vehicle controlling Cloud City during that player's control phase. Character here lost if new character arrives. Effect lost if Cloud City lost. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Weather Vane
Gametext: Deploy on table. Any character here may be captured or rescued by a player's starship or vehicle controlling Cloud City during that player's control phase. Character here lost if new character arrives. Effect lost if Cloud City lost. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Why Didn't You Tell Me?
Gametext: USED: Cancel Noble Sacrifice, Gift Of The Mentor or Old Ben. LOST: If Luke is defending a battle, draw one destiny. Subtract that amount from opponent's attrition and total power (cannot fall below zero).

Title: Wiorkettle
Gametext: Power +1 if with Zutton. During your control phase, may use 1 Force to place one asteroid sector from hand onto Used Pile, search Reserve Deck, take one site into hand and reshuffle.

Title: Wookiee Strangle
Gametext: Use 2 Force to target an opponent's non-droid character present with one of your Wookiees. Both players draw destiny. Add ability and power. Target lost if Wookiee's total destiny > target's total destiny.

Title: You Are Beaten
Gametext: Use 2 Force to target a character present with your warrior with a lightsaber. Target cannot move or battle until end of your next turn. OR Use 1 Force to search your Reserve Deck, take one I Am Your Father into hand and reshuffle. OR Cancel Uncontrollable Fury.

Title: Chewie
Gametext: Must deploy on Hoth, but may move elsewhere. May not be deployed if three or more of opponent's unique (•) characters on table.

Title: Hoth: Mountains (6th Marker)
DarkSideText: Your Imperials and combat vehicles are deploy -1 here.
LightSideText: If you control, Force drain +1 here.

Title: Imperial Walker
Gametext: May add 1 pilot and 8 passengers. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Lone Rogue
Gametext: If one of your pilots is at an exterior Hoth site, use 2 Force to search your Reserve Deck and take one T-47 into hand. OR If your piloted T-47 is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny.

Title: Rebel Snowspeeder
Gametext: May add 1 pilot or passenger. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.

Title: Veers
Gametext: Must deploy on Hoth, but may move elsewhere. May not be deployed if three or more of opponent's unique (•) characters on table. Snowtroopers at same site are forfeit +1.

Title: Walker Garrison
Gametext: If Veers is at an exterior Hoth site, use 2 Force to search your Reserve Deck and take one AT-AT into your hand. Shuffle, cut, and replace. OR If you have 3 AT-ATs at three different Hoth sites, your Force drains are +2 at Hoth locations this turn.

Title: Agents In The Court
Gametext:
While this side up, once per turn you may cancel a Force drain or a just-drawn battle destiny by placing here from hand a copy of your Rep. Once during each of your control phases, you may retrieve a non-unique alien of your Rep's species. When two of your aliens are battling at any Tatooine location, add one destiny to total power. For remainder of game, your Rep may deploy from here as if from hand.
Flip this card if you do not occupy 2 battleground sites.

Title: No Love For The Empire
Gametext:
Deploy Hutt Trade Route and a Jabba's Palace site. May deploy Yarna d'al' Gargan. Reveal one unique (•) alien from your deck whose lore specifies its species. This card is your Rep.
For remainder of game, your Rep is a leader. Yarna d'al' Gargan is immune to Alter. You may not deploy 'insert' cards or operatives. While a rancor is at Rancor Pit, Trap Door is immune to Bo Shuda.
Flip this card if you occupy two battleground sites (must occupy a third with a non-unique alien of your Rep's species if a non-Tatooine location is on table).

Title: Hutt Influence
Gametext: Deploy on table. Opponent may not cancel or modify Force drains at each Tatooine battleground site where you have two aliens with different card titles. Also, attrition against you is reduced by 2 when two of your non-unique aliens with different card titles are in battle.

Title: Jabba's Palace: Antechamber
DarkSideText: Creatures cannot attack here. Force drain -1 here.
LightSideText: Creatures cannot attack here. While no Rebels present, your total power here is +2.

Title: Jabba's Palace: Lower Passages
DarkSideText: During your move phase, your aliens may move between here and any Jabba's Palace site.
LightSideText: While your Lando here, opponent's Lower Passages game text is canceled. Force drain -1 here.

Title: Lando With Vibro-Ax
Gametext: Deploys -2 on Tatooine. When at a Tatooine site, adds one battle destiny. Permanent weapon is vibro-ax (may target character for free; both players draw destiny; target excluded from battle if your destiny +4 > target's power + opponent's destiny).

Title: Mercenary Pilot
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots or drives. When driving a transport vehicle, adds one battle destiny. When piloting at a cloud sector, once per turn may add one battle destiny during battle at a related exterior site.

Title: Mighty Jabba
Gametext: Deploys -2 to a Jabba's Palace site. When with your alien leader, adds one battle destiny. May escort a captive. To use his landspeed requires +1 Force. May not be targeted by weapons unless your other aliens present are each 'hit'. Immune to attrition < 4.

Title: My Kind Of Scum
Gametext:
While this side up, once per turn you may cancel a Force drain or a just-drawn battle destiny by placing here from hand a copy of your Rep. Once during each of your control phases, you may retrieve a non-unique alien of your Rep's species. While Jabba and Bib on table, your battle destiny draws are each +2. Wounded Wookiee is destiny +3. Unless a non-Tatooine location is on table, your aliens are forfeit +2. For remainder of game, your Rep may deploy from here as if from hand.
Flip this card if you do not occupy 2 battleground sites.

Title: Fearless And Inventive
Gametext:
Deploy Desert Heart and a Jabba's Palace site. May deploy Well Guarded. Reveal one unique (•) alien from your deck whose lore specifies its species. This card is your Rep.
For remainder of game, your Rep is a leader. Well Guarded is immune to Alter. You may not deploy 'insert' cards or operatives. While frozen Han on table, Rebels are immune to No Bargain and Bad Feeling Have I.
Flip this card if you occupy two battleground sites (must occupy a third with a non-unique alien of your Rep's species if a non-Tatooine location is on table).

Title: No Escape
Gametext: Deploy on table. You may immediately take top card of Lost Pile into hand. Effects, Epic Events, and Objectives are immune to Honor Of The Jedi. At each opponent's ♢ site, your characters and vehicles are each deploy -3 and your Force generation is +1. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Ounee Ta
Gametext: Deploy on table. You may immediately take top card of Lost Pile into hand. None Shall Pass is unique (•) and a Lost Interrupt. At each opponent's ♢ site, your characters and vehicles are each deploy -3 and your Force generation is +1. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Palace Raider
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (or 3 to power of anything he drives). When driving a transport vehicle, it moves for free and he adds one battle destiny.

Title: Power Of The Hutt
Gametext: Deploy on table. Once during each of your turns, may deploy one Boelo, Bib, Ephant Mon, Jabba's Sail Barge, Jabba's Space Cruiser, or Hutt Influence from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Also, your aliens aboard Jabba's Sail Barge are immune to attrition < 6. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Racing Skiff
Gametext: May deploy with a driver (must be Barada, Klaatu, or a non-unique alien) as a 'react'. May add 1 driver and 3 passengers. May move as a 'react'. If lost, any characters aboard may "jump off" (disembark).

Title: Racing Skiff
Gametext: May deploy with a non-unique alien driver as a 'react'. May add 1 driver and 3 passengers. May move as a 'react'. If lost, any characters aboard may "jump off" (disembark).

Title: Seeking An Audience
Gametext: Deploy on table. Once during each of your turns, may deploy one Underworld Contacts, [Jabba's Palace] Lando, [Jabba's Palace] Leia, R2-D2, or C-3PO from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Also, while Luke is at a Jabba's Palace site, opponent's aliens there must use +1 Force to use their landspeed.

Title: Stun Blaster
Gametext: Deploy on your warrior. May target a character or creature (except rancor or Sarlacc) using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Return character (and cards deployed on character) to owner's hand if destiny +1 > defense value. Creature lost if destiny +3 > defense value.

Title: Stun Blaster
Gametext: Deploy on your warrior. May target a character or creature (except rancor or Sarlacc) using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Return character (and cards deployed on character) to owner's hand if destiny +1 > defense value. Creature lost if destiny +3 > defense value.

Title: Tatooine: Desert Heart
DarkSideText: Your character movement from here (except for Jawas) requires +1 landspeed.
LightSideText: Your character movement from here (except for Jawas) requires +1 landspeed.

Title: Tatooine: Hutt Trade Route (Desert)
DarkSideText: Unless you control Hutt Trade Route, your game text on Tatooine: Jabba's Palace is canceled.
LightSideText: Your characters here aboard vehicles are each power +1.

Title: Underworld Contacts
Gametext: Deploy on a Tatooine site. Your Force generation here is +1. Opponent may not cancel or modify Force drains at each Tatooine battleground site where you have two aliens with different card titles. At any time, you may use 2 Force to raise your converted Tatooine site to top.

Title: 3,720 To 1
Gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost and up to the three lowest destiny numbers of each player's characters on table are totaled. Player with lower total loses Force equal to the difference. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: 4-LOM
Gametext: Total power at same site is +1 for each of your alien/droid pairs present. Once during each battle, if present with Zuckuss, may use 1 Force to search any Used Pile and relocate one character there to the lost pile. May initiate battle and be battled.

Title: 4-LOM's Concussion Rifle
Gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on your warrior, free on 4-LOM. May target a character or creature for free at same site or exterior site up to 2 sites away. Draw destiny. Add 1 if Blaster Scope attached. If total destiny - distance to target > defense value, target hit.

Title: A Dangerous Time
Gametext: USED: Peek at the cards in opponent's Force pile. Reorder however you wish and replace. LOST: Take one Dark Forces into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: A Jedi's Strength
Gametext: *Deploy on an unoccupied Dagobah site. At the beginning of each of your move phases, opponent may relocate this Jedi Test to an adjacent site. *Target a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #1. Apprentice may move only by using personal landspeed. *Attempt when apprentice is present at the beginning of your control phase. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 13, test completed: *Place on apprentice. Apprentice is power +1 and may move normally. Total ability of 6 or more is required for opponent to draw battle destiny.

Title: Anger, Fear, Aggression
Gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost, but opponent must initiate a battle by the end of opponent's next battle phase or lose 4 Force. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Anoat
DarkSideText: If opponent initiates a battle here, your starships may move as a 'react' to or from nearest related asteroid sector.
LightSideText: If you control, all opponent's Ugnaughts on table are forfeit -1.

Title: Anoat
DarkSideText: Your Ugnaughts deploy free aboard starships here. If you control, all your Ugnaughts on table are forfeit +2.
LightSideText: If opponent initiates a battle here, your starships may move as a 'react' to or from nearest related asteroid sector.

Title: Apology Accepted
Gametext: At the end of any battle phase, lose one of your Imperials of ability < 6 who survived a battle you lost this turn. Activate Force up to either that character's forfeit value or the amount of your battle damage in that battle (your choice).

Title: Asteroid Field
DarkSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drain at related system.
LightSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.

Title: Asteroid Field
DarkSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.
LightSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drain at related system.

Title: Asteroid Sanctuary
Gametext: Deploy on any asteroid sector you control. During each of your control phases, opponent loses X Force, where X = total number of asteroid sectors at same system that are not occupied by opponent. Effect canceled if opponent controls this location.

Title: Asteroids Do Not Concern Me
Gametext: Deploy on any asteroid sector. Target one opponent's capital starship. Pilots aboard target may not use ability to draw battle destiny. Subtract 4 from asteroid destiny when targeting that starship. Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.

Title: Astromech Translator
Gametext: Deploy on your starfighter. While an astromech character is aboard: If not piloted, starfighter may move and may use power, maneuver and hyperspeed. OR If piloted, starfighter is immune to attrition < 3 (< 6 if matching pilot aboard).

Title: At Peace
Gametext: Deploy on an apprentice at the beginning of your turn. Apprentice 'rests' (may not attempt Jedi Tests) until end of your next turn, then relocate Immediate Effect to Jedi Test. When attempting this test, that apprentice adds 3 to training destiny. (Immune to Control.)

Title: Avenger
Gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles, and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Subtract 2 from asteroid destiny draws targeting Avenger.

Title: Away Put Your Weapon
Gametext: USED: If a lightsaber was just used to enhance a Force drain, place it in owner's Used Pile. LOST: Place any or all of your devices and character weapons on table in your Used Pile.

Title: Awwww, Cannot Get Your Ship Out
Gametext: Deploy on a landed starship (not at a docking bay). Starship may not move. OR Deploy on a starship or vehicle on Dagobah. Starship or vehicle may not move. At the start of you next control phase, starship or vehicle 'sinks' to the Used Pile.

Title: Bad Feeling Have I
Gametext: Deploy on opponent's side of table. Luke, Leia, Han, Chewie, Lando, Yoda, and Obi-Wan are each deploy +2. Also, opponent may not play any cards with the words "bad feeling" in the title.

Title: Big One
DarkSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. Force drain +1 here for each Asteroid Field at same system.
LightSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.

Title: Big One
DarkSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
LightSideText: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, Force drain +1 here for each Asteroid Field at same system.

Title: Big One: Asteroid Cave or Space Slug Belly
DarkSideText: "Cave Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drains at system related to Big One.
LightSideText: "Cave Rules" in effect here.

Title: Big One: Asteroid Cave or Space Slug Belly
DarkSideText: "Cave Rules" in effect here.
LightSideText: "Cave Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drains at system related to Big One.

Title: Blasted Varmints
Gametext: Use 1 Force to cause all Mynocks or Vine Snakes to detach from one starfighter or character. OR Cause one Mynock attached to any starfighter to be lost. OR After a creature has selected a target character, cancel that selection and select again.

Title: Bog-wing
Gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 1. Habitat: Dagobah. Parasite: Character (that can move). Relocate Bog-wing and host up to two sites away (opponent of victim chooses). Bog-wing then detaches.

Title: Bog-wing
Gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 1. Habitat: Dagobah. Parasite: Character (that can move). Relocate Bog-wing and host up to two sites away (opponent of victim chooses). Bog-wing then detaches.

Title: Bombing Run
Gametext: Deploy on a non-interior planet site (except Dagobah). May move to an adjacent non-interior site at start of your move phase. Your bombers at a related system you control may move to this site. Bombers must return to system at end of your battle phase (if possible).

Title: Bossk
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Hound's Tooth, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Adds 1 to attrition against opponent in battles at same site. May reduce Chewie's forfeit to zero here.

Title: Bossk's Mortar Gun
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on Bossk, 4 on your other warrior. May fire using 2 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny > 0, one card with that destiny number at same site is lost (your choice). If destiny = 0, mortar gun explodes and warrior firing it is lost.

Title: Broken Concentration
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Apprentices subtract X from training destiny, where X = ability - Jedi Test number (minimum zero). Also, once per turn, you may use 2 Force to move the top card of opponent's Force Pile to the top of opponent's Reserve Deck.

Title: Captain Needa
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Avenger, that starship is also immune to attrition < 4. You may re-target applicable Utinni Effects to Needa. If in a battle where you choose to forfeit characters, you must forfeit Needa first.

Title: Close Call
Gametext: USED: Cancel one asteroid destiny and cause it to be drawn again. LOST: Lose 1 Force. Opponent must reveal the top card of Reserve Deck, Force Pile and Used Pile. Card(s) with lowest destiny number greater than zero are lost.

Title: Closer?!
Gametext: During your move phase, use 1 Force to relocate your starship (free if a smuggler aboard) from a planet system to any related asteroid sector (or vice versa). OR Cancel Rogue Asteroid or Close Call.

Title: Comm Chief
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots, and that starship or vehicle moves for free.

Title: Commander Brandei
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Once during each of your control phases, when aboard a Star Destroyer or at any docking bay, may use 1 Force to take one TIE into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Commander Gherant
Gametext: Once during each of your deploy phases, when aboard Executor, may use 2 Force to take one Executor site into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Commander Nemet
Gametext: Adds 1 to power and maneuver of anything he pilots. Opponent may not 'react' to or from same location.

Title: Control
Gametext: Cancel Sense or Alter. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel one Immediate Effect, Mobile Effect or Force drain.

Title: Control
Gametext: Cancel Sense or Alter. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel one Immediate Effect, Mobile Effect or Force drain.

Title: Corporal Derdram
Gametext: Power +1 when at any Executor site. While at Detention Block Corridor, cancels game text of Detention Block Control Room. May use 1 Force take one IT-O or Hypo into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Corporal Vandolay
Gametext: May use 1 Force to take one Spice Mines Of Kessel or Detention Block Corridor into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While Vandolay is at a mobile site, We Have A Prisoner is a Used Interrupt.

Title: Corrosive Damage
Gametext: Deploy on Space Slug Belly. At the end of each player's turn, for every character and starship that player has present, that player must lose 1 Force. Effect canceled if Space Slug lost.

Title: Dagobah
DarkSideText: Neither player may Force drain here.
LightSideText: During your deploy phase, you may deploy one Dagobah site directly from Reserve Deck. Shuffle, cut and replace.

Title: Dagobah: Bog Clearing
DarkSideText: If you occupy, Force generation +1 for you here.
LightSideText: Your starfighters may deploy here and are immune to Awwww, Cannot Get Your Ship Out here.

Title: Dagobah: Cave
DarkSideText: If opponent occupies, your Force icons here are canceled.
LightSideText: Lose 1 force during each of your control phases if Yoda on table but not on Dagobah.

Title: Dagobah: Jungle
DarkSideText: No starships or vehicles here. If you occupy, Force generation +1 for you here.
LightSideText: No starships or vehicles here. Your creatures are deploy -2 here.

Title: Dagobah: Swamp
DarkSideText: At end of your turn, your starships and vehicles here 'sink' to bottom of Lost Pile.
LightSideText: At end of your turn, your starships and vehicles here 'sink' to Used Pile.

Title: Dagobah: Training Area
DarkSideText: You may use 1 Force to cancel any Force drain here.
LightSideText: Once per turn, may take one Jedi Test into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Dagobah: Yoda's Hut
DarkSideText: If you occupy, opponent's Yoda's Hut game text is canceled.
LightSideText: If Yoda here, once per turn, may subtract 2 from attrition against you at another location.

Title: Defensive Fire
Gametext: Cancel Rogue Asteroid. OR Randomly select one card from opponent's hand and place it, unseen, in Used Pile.

Title: Dengar
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Power +1 for each opponent's character present. While present, may reduce Han's forfeit to zero here.

Title: Dengar's Blaster Carbine
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on Dengar, 3 on your other warrior. May target a character, creature, or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. If hit by Dengar, target's forfeit = 0.

Title: Descent Into The Dark
Gametext: During your turn, if either player just placed a card in a Used Pile, deploy on table. All Used Piles are immediately re-circulated. When any player places one or more cards in a Used Pile, Immediate Effect canceled.

Title: Do, Or Do Not
Gametext: Deploy on table. Sense and Alter are Lost Interrupts. Also, when any player makes a destiny draw for Sense or Alter, and that destiny draw is successful, that player loses 2 Force. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Domain Of Evil
Gametext: *Deploy on Dagobah: Jungle or Dagobah: Cave. *Target a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #2. *Attempt when apprentice is present at the end of your turn and none of your cards participated in battles, Force drains or Jedi Tests during that turn. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 14, test completed. *Place on apprentice. You may subtract 1 from each of opponent's destiny draws.

Title: Dragonsnake
Gametext: * Ferocity = 3 + destiny. Habitat: swamps, jungles and Dark Waters. May attack droids. Defeated droids are relocated to an adjacent exterior site (opponent of victim chooses).

Title: Droid Sensorscope
Gametext: Deploy on your R-unit droid. During any control phase, you may use 1 Force to peek at the top card of opponent's Reserve Deck. Also, if on Dagobah, droid may move for free.

Title: Effective Repairs
Gametext: USED: Cancel Limited Resources. LOST: Use 3 Force to retrieve into hand one Effect of any kind.

Title: Egregious Pilot Error
Gametext: During opponent's control phase, if opponent has two or more capital starships at a system or sector together, draw destiny. If destiny - 1 < number of those starships, they may not move or participate in battle until end of your next turn.

Title: Encampment
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any exterior planet site where you have a Rebel or alien. You may deploy characters at this site, even without presence, regardless of location deployment restrictions.

Title: Executor
Gametext: May add unlimited pilots, passengers, vehicles and starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilots provide total ability of 3. Immune to attrition < 12.

Title: Executor: Comm Station
DarkSideText: If you occupy with Tarkin, Piett or any admiral, your starships may 'react' to \ul Executor's\ul0  location.
LightSideText: If you control, your starships may move away from battle at \ul Executor's\ul0  location as a 'react'.

Title: Executor: Control Station
DarkSideText: If an Imperial leader here, \ul Executor\ul0  is power +1 for each \ul Executor\ul0  site on table.
LightSideText: If you control, only you may move \ul Executor\ul0  during opponent's move phase.

Title: Executor: Holotheatre
DarkSideText: If Vader or Emperor on table, your Force generation is +1 here (+2 if both).
LightSideText: Force drain +1 here.

Title: Executor: Main Corridor
DarkSideText: During your move phase, you may move free between here and \ul Executor\ul0  or any \ul Executor\ul0  site.
LightSideText: If you control, opponent's Main Corridor game text is canceled.

Title: Executor: Meditation Chamber
DarkSideText: If Vader alone here, once per turn, may apply his ability to draw battle destiny at any system.
LightSideText: If you occupy, opponent's Meditation Chamber game text is canceled.

Title: Failure At The Cave
Gametext: Deploy on Dagobah: Cave. Target an apprentice on Dagobah. All Jedi Test game text is suspended. If target present during any battle phase, opponent draws destiny. If destiny < 4, you retrieve 2 Force (also, if destiny = 0, target is lost). Otherwise, Utinni Effect canceled.

Title: Fear
Gametext: Opponent must choose to lose either 2 Force from hand or 1 Force from top of Reserve Deck.

Title: Field Promotion
Gametext: Deploy on an Imperial of ability < 5 present with Vader, Emperor or one of your admirals, generals, or moffs. Imperial gains leader skill, is power +1, and is immune to Demotion, Report to Lord Vader, and What is Thy Bidding, My Master?. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Flagship
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. Your other starships may move as a 'react' to same system or sector (for free). If starship lost, you lose X Force, where X = starship's armor. (Immune to your Alter.)

Title: Flash Of Insight
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. At any time, you may use 3 Force to draw the top card of your Reserve Deck into your hand. If that card is a space creature, you may immediately deploy it for free.

Title: Found Someone You Have
Gametext: If you have a character of ability > 4 on table, use 3 Force to find one of your missing characters (your choice). OR During any control phase, examine the top card of your Lost Pile. If that card is a character of ability < 3, take that character into hand.

Title: Frustration
Gametext: During your control phase, peek at opponent's hand and target one non-Interrupt card you find there that has a deploy cost < total number of [Light Side Force] icons on table. Opponent must deploy a card of that title by the end of your next turn, or lose a card of that title from hand (if possible).

Title: Great Warrior
Gametext: *Deploy on a Dagobah site. *Target a mentor here. Also, target or deploy (regardless of location deployment restrictions) an apprentice here. *Attempt when targets are present at the beginning of your control phase. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 12, test completed: *Place on apprentice. All opponent's Force drain bonuses are canceled. Mentor: Your character of ability > 2. Apprentice: Your non-droid, non-Jedi character of lesser ability than mentor. Each time you complete any Jedi Test, you may exchange one card in hand for one Jedi Test in your Lost Pile.\ul

Title: Grounded Starfighter
Gametext: Deploy on a landed starship (not at a docking bay). Starship may not move. OR Deploy on a starship or vehicle on Dagobah. Starship or vehicle may not move. At the start of your next control phase, starship or vehicle 'sinks' to bottom of the Lost Pile.

Title: Han's Toolkit
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on one of you characters, vehicles or starships (free on Falcon or Han). While aboard a vehicle or starship, you may use 1 Force to cancel any Interrupt or Effect of any kind which targets that vehicle or starship.

Title: He Is Not Ready
Gametext: Deploy on opponent's character. Subtracts 2 from that character's training destiny draws. OR Deploy on an opponent's pilot at a site. During each of opponent's move phases, opponent must choose to move that character, lose that character or lose 1 Force.

Title: Hiding In The Garbage
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your side of table. At any time, you may declare a card type. Use your Force one by one, revealing each card used, until a card of that type is revealed (take it into hand) or Force Pile is depleted.

Title: HoloNet Transmission
Gametext: USED: Cancel Transmission Terminated. LOST: Take one Imperial or Visage Of The Emperor into hand from Used Pile; reshuffle.

Title: Hound's Tooth
Gametext: Deploys and moves like a starfighter. May add 1 pilot (must be smuggler or bounty hunter), 6 passengers and 1 vehicle. Immune to attrition < 4 while Bossk piloting. Has ship-docking capability.

Title: I Have A Bad Feeling About This
Gametext: Use 3 Force: Retarget an Interrupt or Utinni Effect which specifies a target to another appropriate target on the same side of the Force. OR Relocate any Effect (except those immune to Alter) deployed on a location to another appropriate location.

Title: I Want That Ship
Gametext: Deploy on one opponent's unique (•) starship at a location you do not occupy. When starship is targeted by any tractor beam or ion cannon, subtract 2 from maneuver. If starship is captured or lost, lose Effect and opponent must lose 3 Force (5 if Falcon).

Title: IG-2000
Gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 2 passengers. Maneuver +3 and immune to attrition < 3 if IG-88 piloting. Ion Cannon may deploy aboard.

Title: IG-88
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May 'assassinate' any character at same site hit by IG-88 (victim is immediately lost). May use two different weapons. May initiate battle and be battled. Immune to Restraining Bolt and purchase.

Title: IG-88's Neural Inhibitor
Gametext: Deploy on IG-88, or use 2 Force to deploy on any other bounty hunter. May target a non-droid character using 3 Force. Draw destiny. Target is power, forfeit and landspeed = 0 until end of your next turn if destiny +1 > ability.

Title: IG-88's Pulse Cannon
Gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on IG-88, 4 on your other warrior. Adds 2 to power. May target X non-droid characters or creatures using X Force. Draw destiny for each. If destiny = 0, character is power -1 and forfeit -1 until end of turn. If destiny -1 > defense value, target hit.

Title: Imbalance
Gametext: If opponent just retrieved Force, opponent must lose X Force, where X = one-half the number of cards retrieved (round up).

Title: Imperial Helmsman
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a Star Destroyer, also draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

Title: Ineffective Maneuver
Gametext: Deploy on any Effect or Utinni Effect (except those immune to Alter). During each of owner's draw phases, if you occupy an asteroid sector, owner must choose to either lose 1 Force or voluntarily cancel that Effect or Utinni Effect. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: It Is The Future You See
Gametext: *Deploy on a Dagobah site. *Target a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #4. *Attempt when apprentice is present at the beginning of your control phase. Turn apprentice upside down (cannot move and power = 0). At the end of your next turn, turn apprentice right side up (restored): *Place on apprentice. Immune to attrition < 4. Reveal the top two cards of your Reserve Deck and place one upside down on apprentice. Whenever you are about to draw a card for destiny, you may instead use the upside-down card (which remains on apprentice for re-use).

Title: Jedi Levitation
Gametext: Use X Force, where X = (7 - ability of your highest-ability character on table). Take one card from Used Pile into hand; reshuffle.

Title: Knowledge And Defense
Gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost and opponent may not initiate any battles for remainder of turn. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Landing Claw
Gametext: Deploy on your starfighter. During any control phase, may target one opponent's capital starship present. Starfighter attaches to target (automatically moves with target and is 'concealed'). May detach at any time (even as target begins to move).

Title: Lando System?
Gametext: During your control phase, use 1 Force to move one of your [Dagobah] characters of ability > 1 to any [Cloud City] location where you have presence. If moving to a Cloud City site, this movement is free and you do not need presence.

Title: Levitation
Gametext: USED: Cancel Silence is Golden or Shut Him Up Or Shut Him Down. LOST: Take any one droid, device or Stone Pile into hand from Used Pile; reshuffle.

Title: Lieutenant Commander Ardan
Gametext: When at a site, may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Immune to attrition < X, where X = number of opponent's aliens present.

Title: Lieutenant Suba
Gametext: While at a Death Star or Executor site, your troopers deploy free there and are power and forfeit +1 there, and may use 1 Force to take one Tactical Support into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Lieutenant Venka
Gametext: Power +2 when at an Executor site or same site as Tarkin or Chief Bast, or if the Death Star has been "blown away." Fear Will Keep Them In Line is destiny +2 and, when it adds 1 to your power, also adds 1 to attrition against opponent.

Title: Light Maneuvers
Gametext: Cancel Dark Maneuvers, Emergency Deployment, Lone Pilot, I Want That Ship, Defensive Fire, Rogue Asteroid or Take Evasive Action. OR Double Special Modifications until end of turn.

Title: Location, Location, Location
Gametext: Deploy on table. At the end of each player's deploy phase, if they did not deploy a location, they lose 1 Force. Effect canceled if any player deploys three or more locations in a single turn.

Title: Lost In Space
Gametext: If a pilot was just lost from a system or sector, deploy on that location and stack pilot here. Pilot may be rescued or captured by any capital starship present here during any move phase, and may be targeted by wespons (except during battle) as if present (treat as a starfighter with defense value = 0). Lost if no pilot here.

Title: Lost Relay
Gametext: Target one opponent's starfighter present with your starship at an asteroid sector, before asteroid destiny is drawn this turn. If target lost this turn due to asteroid destiny, opponent also loses Force equal to target's forfeit value.

Title: Luke's Backpack
Gametext: Deploy on your character. May carry and use any number of devices. May also carry Yoda, Kabe or any one Jawa or Ewok (as if riding a creature vehicle). Adds 1 to training destiny when carrying the mentor.

Title: Mist Hunter
Gametext: May add 2 pilots (one must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 3 passengers. Immune to attrition < 3 if Zuckuss piloting. Has ship-docking capability.

Title: Moving To Attack Position
Gametext: Target one starfighter participating in a battle at a system or sector. For remainder of turn, starfighter may not move, is immune to attrition and, if piloted by any Corellian, is power +2.

Title: Much Anger In Him
Gametext: Deploy on a Rebel. At the end of each of opponent's battle phases, if you have presence at the location where that Rebel has presences and a battle did not take place there, opponent loses 4 Force.

Title: Mynock
Gametext: Habitat: unlimited. Parasite: Starfighter. Host's power and hyperspeed are cumulatively -2; while both < 1, Mynocks randomly detach one at a time (cannot attach for remainder of turn). Moves like a starfighter.

Title: Mynock
Gametext: Habitat: unlimited. Parasite: Starfighter. Host's power and hyperspeed are cumulatively -2; while both < 1, Mynocks randomly detach one at a time (cannot attach for remainder of turn). Moves like a starfighter.

Title: Never Tell Me The Odds
Gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost and up to the three lowest destiny numbers of each player's characters on table are totaled. Player with lower total loses Force equal to the difference. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: No Disintegrations!
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your side of table. If a Rebel of ability > 2 is lost (not captured) during a battle involving an opponent's bounty hunter, opponent loses 3 Force. If Vader on table, one bounty hunter involved in that battle (your choice) is also lost.

Title: Nudj
Gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 4. Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth and Tatooine) and Dark Waters. Cumulatively absorbs (temporarily cancels) one (Dark Side Force icon) icon present. Parasite: None.

Title: Obi-Wan's Apparition
Gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy at any site if opponent is generating at least 3 Force more than you. At that site, adjacent sites and same sites as Obi-Wan, players activate Force only if they have presence.

Title: Order To Engage
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. At the end of each of opponent's battle phases, if a battle did not take place at every location where both players have presence at the end of that phase, opponent loses 3 Force.

Title: Polarized Negative Power Coupling
Gametext: Deploy on table. Turn every Used Pile face up. All subsequent cards placed in Used Piles are also turned face up. (Players must commit to using cards before revealing them.) Turn used cards face down whenever they are re-circulated.

Title: Portable Fusion Generator
Gametext: Deploy on your warrior. When that warrior fires a blaster rifle or artillery weapon, adds 1 to each of that weapon's destiny draws. Also, may add 1 to power of one droid present.

Title: Precision Targeting
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on table. Any card which is 'hit' may not be used to satisfy attrition. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Proton Bombs
Gametext: Deploy on a bomber. When you Force drain at same system, may target a related interior site. Draw destiny. Site 'collapsed' if destiny > 4. May fire in Bombing Run battle. Draw destiny. All characters, starships and vehicles with that destiny number at same site are lost.

Title: Punishing One
Gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 1 passenger. Immune to attrition < 3 if Dengar piloting. Deploy -3 when deploying with Dengar. Boosted TIE Cannon may deploy aboard.

Title: Quick Draw
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Once during each of your draw phases, you may use 2 Force to take any one blaster from your Lost pile and deploy it (for free).

Title: Raithal
DarkSideText: All your troopers are destiny +1 (+2 if you control). Tactical Support is a Used Interrupt.
LightSideText: If you occupy, opponent's Raithal game text is canceled.

Title: Raithal
DarkSideText: If you control, you may raise your converted Raithal system to the top.
LightSideText: If you control, all opponent's troopers are forfeit and destiny -1.

Title: Rebel Flight Suit
Gametext: Deploy on your pilot character. While piloting any starfighter, combat vehicle or shuttle vehicle, that character is considered to be the "matching pilot" (pilot adds 2 to maneuver (limit +2) and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise).

Title: Recoil In Fear
Gametext: Use 3 Force. Each player places hand onto Reserve Deck (if possible), then places Used Pile onto Reserve deck; reshuffle. Each player then draws cards from Reserve Deck equal to the number of cards just placed from hand onto Reserve Deck (if any).

Title: Reflection
Gametext: Deploy on Leia. Once during each of your control phases, you may use 3 Force to retrieve 1 Force. Also, when an apprentice, adds 1 to her training destiny.

Title: Report To Lord Vader
Gametext: If you just won a battle, deploy on Vader. Target an Imperial involved in that battle. Vader and target are power and forfeit -4. When target reaches Vader, lose Utinni Effect and draw destiny. If destiny > 2, target lost.

Title: Res Luk Ra'auf
Gametext: If any bounty hunter is defending a battle alone, add one battle destiny. OR If Bossk, Greedo or Boba Fett is defending a battle alone, add two battle destiny.

Title: Retractable Arm
Gametext: Deploy on your R-unit droid to give that droid thief skill. Once during each of your control phases, you may use 1 Force to target a weapon or device present. Draw destiny. If destiny > 2, target is 'stolen.' Target may then be transferred for free. Droid may not be Disarmed.

Title: Rogue Asteroid
Gametext: Deploy on an asteroid sector and specify starting direction. Every move phase, moves to next adjacent asteroid sector (reversing direction as necessary). Where present, adds 2 to asteroid destiny. May be targeted by starship weapons (defense value= 3).

Title: Rogue Asteroid
Gametext: Deploy on an asteroid sector and specify starting direction. Every move phase, moves to next adjacent asteroid sector (reversing direction as necessary). Where present, adds 2 to asteroid destiny. May be targeted by starship weapons (defense value = 3).

Title: Rycar's Run
Gametext: Deploy on a Big One. X = twice the number of asteroid sectors at that system. Target a starfighter at related planet system. When reached by target, relocate Utinni Effect to planet system. When target returns to system, lose Utinni Effect. Retrieve X Force.

Title: Scramble
Gametext: Deploy on opponent's side of table. Opponent's pilots (except Vader) present at sites may not use ability to draw battle destiny. Effect canceled when opponent has no pilots at sites.

Title: Shoo! Shoo!
Gametext: If you have a droid on table: Cancel an attack just initiated by a creature. OR Move one opponent's creature (except an attached creature) to an adjacent location (habitat permitting).

Title: Shot In The Dark
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Once per turn, you may lose 1 Force to draw the top card of your Reserve Deck into your hand. If that card is a space creature, you may immediately deploy it for free.

Title: Shut Him Up Or Shut Him Down
Gametext: Cancel Death Star Plans, The Professor, Bacta Tank, How Did We Get Into This Mess?, Shoo! Shoo! or Thank The Maker.

Title: Size Matters Not
Gametext: *Deploy on Dagobah: Swamp or Dagobah: Bog Clearing. *Target a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #3. *Attempt when apprentice is present at the beginning of your control phase. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 15, test completed: *Place on apprentice. Immune to attrition < 3. Once during each of your control phases, you may use 2 Force to take any one card into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Sleen
Gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 3. Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth and Tatooine) and Dark Waters. Cumulatively absorbs (temporarily cancels) one (Light Side Force icon) icon present. Parasite: None.

Title: Smuggler's Blues
Gametext: Deploy on a smuggler. May use 2 Force to cancel Limited Resources. Also, if 'trained' by Rycar Ryjerd and piloting a starship when that starship completes Kessel Run, Rycar's Run or The First Transport Is Away, any retrieved Force may be taken into hand.

Title: Something Hit Us!
Gametext: During a battle, lose 1 Force. Cumulatively adds 1 to attrition against opponent.

Title: Son Of Skywalker
Gametext: Deploys only on Dagobah or Cloud City. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Once per game, during your deploy phase, a lightsaber may deploy on Luke (for free) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 4.

Title: Space Slug
Gametext: * Ferocity = two destiny. Habitat: Big One (Cave is now Belly). Attacks starfighters (defeated cards are eaten or relocated to Belly, opponent of victim chooses). Once per turn, may open or close mouth.

Title: Space Slug
Gametext: * Ferocity = two destiny. Habitat: Big One (Cave is now Belly). Attacks starfighters (defeated cards are eaten or relocated to Belly, opponent of victim chooses). Once per turn, may open or close mouth.

Title: Star Destroyer: Launch Bay
DarkSideText: Your TIEs deploy -2 here. You may shuttle, transfer, embark and disembark here for free.
LightSideText: Starships captured by Star Destroyer go here and may be Besieged. Immune to Revolution.

Title: Starship Levitation
Gametext: USED: Cancel Awwww, Cannot Get Your Ship Out. LOST: Use 1 Force to draw destiny. If destiny < ability of you highest-ability character on table, take one starship into hand from Used Pile; reshuffle.

Title: Stone Pile
Gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Dagobah site. Randomly select two cards from opponent's hand and place them, unseen, face down beneath Stone Pile. Cards return to opponent's hand if Effect leaves table. Canceled if opponent occupies this site.

Title: Sudden Impact
Gametext: Deploy on any Effect or Utinni Effect (except those immune to Alter). Once during each of owner's draw phases, if you occupy an asteroid sector, owner must choose to either lose 1 Force or lose that Effect or Utinni Effect. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Take Evasive Action
Gametext: Cancel Egregious Pilot Error, Out Of Nowhere, Collision! or Don't Get Cocky. OR Use 1 Force to subtract 3 from all asteroid destiny draws against you for remainder of turn.

Title: The Dark Path
Gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Once per turn, you may peek at the top three cards of your Reserve Deck. Place any two of those three in your Lost Pile.

Title: The Professor
Gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on your side of table (free if C-3PO on table). If you have a protocol droid aboard a starship or vehicle in a battle, you may use X Force to reduce the battle damage against you by X (by X+1 if a astromech character is also aboard).

Title: There Is No Try
Gametext: Deploy on table. Sense and Alter are Lost Interrupts. Also, when any player makes a destiny draw for Sense or Alter, and that destiny draw is successful, that player loses 2 Force. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: They'd Be Crazy To Follow Us
Gametext: Use 1 Force to target a starship at an asteroid sector or a "blown away" system. For remainder of turn, you may add 2 to destiny totals targeting the armor or maneuver of that starship.

Title: This Is More Like It
Gametext: During a battle, lose X Force to reduce attrition against you by X. OR Cancel This Is Just Wrong.

Title: This Is No Cave
Gametext: Relocate one starfighter from a Big One to the related site (or vice versa) for free (opens Slug's mouth if closed). If smuggler aboard, starfighter is immune to attrition and subtracts 5 from asteroid destiny until end of your next turn. OR Cancel Corrosive Damage.

Title: Those Rebels Won't Escape Us
Gametext: USED: Cancel Nabrun Leids. LOST: During your move phase, cancel Landing Claw. OR Cancel Hyper Escape, Closer?! or one 'react.'

Title: Through The Force Things You Will See
Gametext: At the end of any player's draw phase, cause that player to place Used Pile face up on top of Reserve Deck; reshuffle. When face up cards are removed from Reserve Deck, they are treated as normal (no longer face up).

Title: TIE Avenger
Gametext: Deploy -1 to same system as any Imperial capital starship. May add 1 pilot. Boosted TIE Cannon may deploy aboard.

Title: TIE Bomber
Gametext: Power +2 during a Bombing Run battle. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. At any time during your turn, may use 1 Force to 'diffuse' (lose or return to hand) any one Orbital Mine present.

Title: Tight Squeeze
Gametext: If you have a lone vehicle or starfighter in a battle or Attack Run at Beggar's Canyon, Cloud City, Death Star: Trench or an asteroid sector, use 1 Force. At the end of that battle or Attack Run, opponent must forfeit two participating vehicles or starfighters.

Title: Transmission Terminated
Gametext: Cancel one hologram. OR Use 3 Force. Draw destiny. Add 1 to destiny for each asteroid sector on table. If total destiny > 3, Imperial Holotable site is "blown away" (opponent loses 4 Force).

Title: Tunnel Vision
Gametext: Take one card into hand from Force pile; reshuffle.

Title: Uncertain Is The Future
Gametext: Use 3 Force. Each player places hand onto Reserve Deck (if possible), then places Used Pile onto Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Each player then draws cards from Reserve Deck equal to the number of cards just placed from hand onto Reserve Deck (if any).

Title: Unexpected Interruption
Gametext: Use 2 Force to take one Interrupt into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Vine Snake
Gametext: Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth). Parasite: Non-droid character. Each move phase, draw destiny; each time destiny > ability, add 1 to X (X starts at 0). Host is power -X (eaten if power = 0).

Title: Vine Snake
Gametext: Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth). Parasite: Non-droid character. Each move phase, draw destiny; each time destiny > ability, add 1 to X (X starts at 0). Host is power -X (eaten if power = 0).

Title: Visage Of The Emperor
Gametext: Lose 2 Force to deploy on Executor: Holotheatre or Death Star: Conference Room. At the end of each player's turn, each player must lose 1 Force. Effect canceled if opponent controls this site. (Immune to Alter.)

Title: Visored Vision
Gametext: Name an Interrupt card. Opponent must reveal entire Used Pile, without shuffling. Then you choose: USED: Opponent must lose 1 Force for each copy of that Interrupt found there. LOST: Each copy of that interrupt found there is lost.

Title: Voyeur
Gametext: Name an Interrupt card. Opponent must reveal entire Used Pile, without shuffling. Then you choose: USED: Opponent must lose 1 Force for each copy of that Interrupt found there. LOST: Each copy of that interrupt found there is lost.

Title: Warrant Officer M'Kae
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May use 1 Force to take one tractor beam, Our First Catch Of The Day or Besieged into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Wars Not Make One Great
Gametext: Deploy on any location. For either player to initiate a battle or Force drain anywhere, that player must use +1 Force. Effect canceled if opponent controls this location.

Title: We Can Still Outmaneuver Them
Gametext: USED: Take one Collision! or Egregious Pilot Error into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. LOST: If opponent just initiated a battle with at least two capital starships where you have a lone starfighter, add two battle destiny.

Title: We Don't Need Their Scum
Gametext: USED: Cancel Res Luk Ra'auf. LOST: If two bounty hunters (or an Imperial and a bounty hunter) are in a battle together, use 2 Force to draw two destiny. Subtract total from opponent's attrition and total power.

Title: WHAAAAAAAAAOOOOW!
Gametext: If your character was just defeated by a Dragonsnake, Rancor, Sarlacc, Dianoga or Wampa, instead of being 'eaten' that character is 'hurled' (relocated) to an adjacent site, if possible.

Title: What Is Thy Bidding, My Master?
Gametext: Deploy on Emperor or any system. Target one character whose lore uses the word 'Emperor.' Target cannot use ability to draw battle destiny and is excluded from being the "highest-ability character." Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.

Title: Yoda
Gametext: Deploy on Dagobah I must, but move elsewhere I may, yes. When the mentor, 1 to training destiny I add. Where present am I, battles and attacks happen not unless present a Dark Side character of ability > 3 there is. To attrition, immune am I.

Title: Yoda Stew
Gametext: During opponent's turn, take up to four cards from your hand and place them on top of your Force Pile.

Title: Yoda, You Seek Yoda
Gametext: Use 1 Force to retrieve Yoda. OR Use 3 Force to take Yoda into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.

Title: Yoda's Gimer Stick
Gametext: Deploy on Yoda. You may initiate battles and attacks where present. OR Use 2 Force to deploy on one of your characters of ability > 3. Immune to attrition. Where present, no battles or attacks may be initiated unless an opponent's character of ability > 3 present.

Title: Yoda's Hope
Gametext: Deploy on a character. When on the mentor, adds 1 to training destiny draws. If on Yoda, you may lose Effect to take one card with 'levitation' in the title from Reserve Deck into hand; reshuffle.

Title: You Do Have Your Moments
Gametext: During a battle, before any cards have been forfeited, reduce all attrition for both sides to zero.

Title: Zuckuss
Gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May move for free as 'react.' Once during each battle, may use 1 Force to cause one alien of ability < 3 at same site to be forfeit = 0 for remainder of turn. Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: Zuckuss' Snare Rifle
Gametext: Deploy on Zuckuss, or use 1 Force to deploy on any other bounty hunter. May target a character or creature using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Character captured if destiny -1 > defense value. Creature lost if destiny +1 > defense value.

Title: Agent Kallus
Gametext: Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots. When deployed, may reveal the top two cards of your Reserve Deck; take one into hand and place the other in Used Pile. While with an ISB agent, adds one battle destiny.

Title: Baniss Keeg, Pilot Instructor
Gametext: Adds 3 to power and 1 to hyperspeed of anything he pilots. Once per turn, if you just deployed a Black Sun Agent to same system, may draw top card of Reserve Deck. Your characters here are immune to Cantina Brawl and Fallen Portal.

Title: Cad Bane
Gametext: Add 2 to the power of anything he pilots. Your other bounty hunters here are power +1. Draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise. During battle, if with your other bounty hunter, may cancel the immunity to attrition of a Jedi here.

Title: Commander Nemet
Gametext: Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots. Once per game, may deploy an Imperial-class Star Destroyer from reserve deck; reshuffle. While piloting Avenger, it is immune to attrition < 4 and during battle may lose an Imperial aboard (or from hand) to cancel a just drawn destiny (causes a redraw if opponent's first battle destiny).

Title: Darth Maul, Lone Hunter
Gametext: Cancels the game text of Amidala, Obi-Wan, and Qui-Gon at same site. While alone, Blaster Deflection is canceled here and Maul's weapon destiny draws may not be modified or canceled by opponent. Immune to attrition < 5.

Title: General Grievous
Gametext: Any stolen lightsaber may deploy on Grievous. Once per game, Grievous may steal a lightsaber from opponent's Lost Pile. Unless alone, may lose 1 Force to return Grievous (and your cards on him) to hand from a site you control. Immune to attrition < 4.

Title: Ortugg
Gametext: While at a Jabba's Palace site, your other Gamorreans are deploy -1 and forfeit +3. Permanent weapon is •Ortugg's Ax (may target a character or creature for free; draw destiny; target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if destiny +1 > defense value).

Title: Deflector Shield Generators
Gametext: Deploy on a capital starship. Starship is power and armor +2 and immune to attrition < 5. May cancel Combined Attack or Power Pivot targeting this starship. Starfighters here may not 'attach'.

Title: Drop!
Gametext: Deploy on table. While no card stacked here, may stack opponent's just-played Interrupt here. Opponent may use 3 Force to place an Interrupt here in Used Pile. Once per turn, may place a card from hand on bottom of Used Pile. [Immune to Alter].

Title: Coruscant
DarkSideText: While you occupy with a Black Sun agent or ISB agent, gains one [Dark Side Force] icon and one [Light Side Force] icon.
LightSideText: While you control, gains one [Light Side Force] icon.

Title: Coruscant: Xizor's Palace
DarkSideText: Black Sun agents move to here for free. Once per turn, may deploy a Xizor's Palace site form reserve deck; reshuffle
LightSideText: Unless Chewie, Dash, or Leia present, Force drain -1 here.

Title: Xizor's Palace: Uplink Station
DarkSideText: If Falleen's Fist at Coruscant and your Black Sun agent here, Force drain +1 here. .

Title: Tatooine
DarkSideText: Opponent may not initiate battle here until after your first turn.
LightSideText: If a player controls, for each of their starships here, their power is +1 in battles at Tatooine sites.

Title: Falleen's Fist
Gametext: Deploys -3 if your Black Sun agent is at a related site. May add 3 pilots and 6 passengers. Permanent pilots provide total ability of 4. Immune to attrition < 8.

Title: Admiral Ackbar
Gametext: Adds 3 to the power of any capital starship he pilots. Deploys free aboard Home One. While piloting a Star Cruiser, adds one battle destiny. Where you have two Rebel capital starships, attrition against opponent is +2.

Title: Captain Raymus Antilles
Gametext: Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots, 3 if a Rebel capital starship. Deploys -1 aboard Tantive IV. While aboard Tantive IV, it is immune to Lateral Damage and attrition < 5.

Title: CT-5555 (Fives)
Gametext: Once per turn, if you just drew a destiny of 5, may take that card into hand. During any deploy phase, may use 1 Force to target a Dark Jedi present. Draw destiny. If destiny = 5, target loses immunity to attrition for remainder of turn.

Title: Ellorrs Madak, Pilot Instructor
Gametext: Adds 3 to the power of anything he pilots. Adds 2 to the hyperspeed of any freighter he pilots. During your move phase, may use 1 Force to "break cover" of opponent's Undercover spy at same site. Lateral Damage is canceled at same or related system.

Title: Endor Commando Team
Gametext: Deploys -1 to Endor. During battle, your other Rebels here may not have their forfeit reduced unless this card 'hit.' Each time this character is 'hit,' it is cumulatively power -2 until end of turn.

Title: Kanan Jarrus
Gametext: Adds 1 to the power of anything he pilots. While present with an Imperial (or two Rebels), all immunity to attrition here is canceled.

Title: Leslomy Tacema
Gametext: Adds 3 to the power of anything he pilots. Smuggler. When piloting a freighter, adds 1 to hyperspeed. Your total ability at same docking bay or system may not be reduced. Once per game, may deploy a card with 'Ellorrs' in title here from reserve deck; reshuffle.

Title: Major Bren Derlin
Gametext: Scout. Deploys free to (and power +2 at) Cantina, Endor, or Hoth. Opponent may not 'react' to or from here. Once per game, may retrieve an Explosive Charge into hand.

Title: Mon Calamari Admiral
Gametext: Adds 2 to the power of any capital starship he pilots. Your Rebel starships may move to here for free. While piloting a Rebel capital starship, opponent may not modify or cancel your battle destinies here.

Title: Padmé Naberrie
Gametext: Cancels Vader's game text here. If with a Skywalker, may add one destiny to attrition. Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: Padmé Naberrie
Gametext: Cancels Vader's game text here. If with a Skywalker, may add one destiny to attrition. Immune to attrition < 3.

Title: R2-D2 & C-3PO
Gametext: If about to leave table from Tatooine system (even from Overwhelmed) and Stolen Data Tapes deployed on this character, may instead be relocated to Dune Sea. Immune to devices. Unless Undercover, immune to opponent's Interrupts.

Title: Toryn Farr
Gametext: Add 2 to the power of anything she pilots. Your total battle destiny here is +1 (+2 if piloting a transport). Once per turn, if a battle just ended, may 'rescue' (retrieve from Lost Pile OR stack on [Set 0] Evacuation Control) a Rebel of ability < 3 forfeited from same location this turn.

Title: Planetary Defenses
Gametext: Plays on any site. This location may not be targeted by Proton Bombs. Cancels Program Trap here. Unless Death Star: Docking Bay 327 on table, Commence Primary Ignition is canceled.

Title: Stolen Data Tapes
Gametext: Deploy on Dune Sea or R2-D2. If about to be lost, relocate to Dune Sea (if possible). If at Dune Sea, may relocate to your character here. If at Alderaan (or a 'blown away' system), schematics 'delivered'; relocate this Effect to table and may take into hand any card from reserve deck; reshuffle. [Immune to Alter.]

Title: The Shield Is Down!
Gametext: Deploy on table. Your scouts move (using landspeed) to and from Back Door for free. Once per turn, may deploy Bunker or an Endor battleground site from reserve deck; reshuffle. While an Explosive Charge at Bunker, flip Rebel Strike Team and Garrison Destroyed may not flip. [Immune to Alter]

Title: Thrown Back
Gametext: Deploy on table. While no card stacked here, may stack opponent's just-played Interrupt here. Opponent may use 3 Force to place an Interrupt here in Used Pile. Once per turn, may place a card from hand on bottom of Used Pile. [Immune to Alter].

Title: Rebel Leadership
Gametext: Take an admiral or general into hand from reserve deck; reshuffle. OR If your admiral is in battle at a system (or your general is in battle at a site), you may either add one battle destiny or prevent opponent from drawing more than one battle destiny.

Title: The Force Is Strong With This One
Gametext: If your Padawan or Skywalker of ability < 6 is in battle with a Dark Jedi, either add one battle destiny or Cancel I Have You Now.

Title: Bright Hope
Gametext: May add 2 pilots and 6 passengers. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. If in battle with another Rebel capital starship, may draw destiny. Subtract that amount from opponent's attrition and total power.

Title: Wild Karrde
Gametext: May add 3 pilots and 6 passengers. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. During battle, your total battle destiny is +1 for each smuggler aboard. Deploys and moves like a starfighter. Immune to attrition < 5.

Title: Diplomatic Mission To Alderaan
Gametext:
While this side up, your total battle destiny is +X, where X = number of battlegrounds occupied by Rebels of ability < 4. Once per turn, may deploy Alderaan or a Tatooine battleground site from Reserve Deck, reshuffle. Once per turn, if you just won a battle, may retrieve 1 Force.
Flip this card if you do not occupy a battleground site and a battleground system (or you do not control any locations).

Title: A Weakness Can Be Found
Gametext:
Deploy Tatooine (with Tantive IV, non-[Ref II] R2-D2, and Stolen Data Tapes there) and Dune Sea.
For remainder of game, you may not deploy Sandwhirl or [Episode I] Jedi.
